00244 static void id_release_weakref_list(struct ID *id, GHash *weakinfo_hash)
00245 {
00246     GHashIterator weakinfo_hash_iter;
00247 
00248     BLI_ghashIterator_init(&weakinfo_hash_iter, weakinfo_hash);
00249 
00250 #ifdef DEBUG_RNA_WEAKREF
00251     fprintf(stdout, "id_release_weakref: '%s', %d items\n", id->name, BLI_ghash_size(weakinfo_hash));
00252 #endif
00253 
00254     while (!BLI_ghashIterator_isDone(&weakinfo_hash_iter)) {
00255         PyObject *weakref = (PyObject *)BLI_ghashIterator_getKey(&weakinfo_hash_iter);
00256         PyObject *item = PyWeakref_GET_OBJECT(weakref);
00257         if (item != Py_None) {
00258 
00259 #ifdef DEBUG_RNA_WEAKREF
00260             PyC_ObSpit("id_release_weakref item ", item);
00261 #endif
00262 
00263             pyrna_invalidate((BPy_DummyPointerRNA *)item);
00264         }
00265 
00266         Py_DECREF(weakref);
00267 
00268         BLI_ghashIterator_step(&weakinfo_hash_iter);
00269     }
00270 
00271     BLI_ghash_remove(id_weakref_pool, (void *)id, NULL, NULL);
00272     BLI_ghash_free(weakinfo_hash, NULL, NULL);
00273 
00274     if (BLI_ghash_size(id_weakref_pool) == 0) {
00275         BLI_ghash_free(id_weakref_pool, NULL, NULL);
00276         id_weakref_pool = NULL;
00277 #ifdef DEBUG_RNA_WEAKREF
00278         printf("id_release_weakref freeing pool\n");
00279 #endif
00280     }

00748  * however there are a few RNA properties that are fake sub-structs and

00752  * So compare the 'ptr->type' as well to avoid this problem.
00753  * It's highly unlikely this would happen that 'ptr->data' and 'ptr->prop' would match,
00754  * but _not_ 'ptr->type' but include this check for completeness.
00755  * - campbell */

00760              (a->ptr.type == b->ptr.type)) ? 0 : -1);

00770 static PyObject *pyrna_struct_richcmp(PyObject *a, PyObject *b, int op)
00771 {
00772     PyObject *res;
00773     int ok = -1; /* zero is true */
00774 
00775     if (BPy_StructRNA_Check(a) && BPy_StructRNA_Check(b))
00776         ok = pyrna_struct_compare((BPy_StructRNA *)a, (BPy_StructRNA *)b);
00777 
00778     switch (op) {
00779         case Py_NE:
00780             ok = !ok; /* pass through */
00781         case Py_EQ:
00782             res = ok ? Py_False : Py_True;
00783             break;
00784 
00785         case Py_LT:
00786         case Py_LE:
00787         case Py_GT:
00788         case Py_GE:
00789             res = Py_NotImplemented;
00790             break;
00791         default:
00792             PyErr_BadArgument();
00793             return NULL;
00794     }
00795 
00796     return Py_INCREF(res), res;
00797 }

01168 /* 'value' _must_ be a set type, error check before calling */
01169 int pyrna_set_to_enum_bitfield(EnumPropertyItem *items, PyObject *value, int *r_value, const char *error_prefix)
01170 {
01171     /* set of enum items, concatenate all values with OR */
01172     int ret, flag = 0;
01173 
01174     /* set looping */
01175     Py_ssize_t pos = 0;
01176     Py_ssize_t hash = 0;
01177     PyObject *key;
01178 
01179     *r_value = 0;
01180 
01181     while (_PySet_NextEntry(value, &pos, &key, &hash)) {
01182         const char *param = _PyUnicode_AsString(key);
01183 
01184         if (param == NULL) {
01185             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
01186                          "%.200s expected a string, not %.200s",
01187                          error_prefix, Py_TYPE(key)->tp_name);
01188             return -1;
01189         }
01190 
01191         if (pyrna_enum_value_from_id(items, param, &ret, error_prefix) < 0) {
01192             return -1;
01193         }
01194 
01195         flag |= ret;
01196     }
01197 
01198     *r_value = flag;
01199     return 0;
01200 }

01205     int ret;
01206     int free = FALSE;
01207 
01208     *r_value = 0;
01209 
01210     if (!PyAnySet_Check(value)) {
01211         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
01212                      "%.200s, %.200s.%.200s expected a set, not a %.200s",
01213                      error_prefix, RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type),
01214                      RNA_property_identifier(prop), Py_TYPE(value)->tp_name);
01215         return -1;
01216     }
01217 
01218     RNA_property_enum_items(BPy_GetContext(), ptr, prop, &item, NULL, &free);
01219 
01220     if (item) {
01221         ret = pyrna_set_to_enum_bitfield(item, value, r_value, error_prefix);
01222     }
01223     else {
01224         if (PySet_GET_SIZE(value)) {
01225             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
01226                          "%.200s: empty enum \"%.200s\" could not have any values assigned",
01227                          error_prefix, RNA_property_identifier(prop));
01228             ret = -1;
01229         }
01230         else {
01231             ret = 0;
01232         }
01233     }
01234 
01235     if (free)
01236         MEM_freeN(item);
01237 
01238     return ret;
01239 }

01333 PyObject *pyrna_prop_to_py(PointerRNA *ptr, PropertyRNA *prop)
01334 {
01335     PyObject *ret;
01336     const int type = RNA_property_type(prop);
01337 
01338     if (RNA_property_array_check(prop)) {
01339         return pyrna_py_from_array(ptr, prop);
01340     }
01341 
01342     /* see if we can coorce into a python type - PropertyType */
01343     switch (type) {
01344         case PROP_BOOLEAN:
01345             ret = PyBool_FromLong(RNA_property_boolean_get(ptr, prop));
01346             break;
01347         case PROP_INT:
01348             ret = PyLong_FromSsize_t((Py_ssize_t)RNA_property_int_get(ptr, prop));
01349             break;
01350         case PROP_FLOAT:
01351             ret = PyFloat_FromDouble(RNA_property_float_get(ptr, prop));
01352             break;
01353         case PROP_STRING:
01354         {
01355             const int subtype = RNA_property_subtype(prop);
01356             const char *buf;
01357             int buf_len;
01358             char buf_fixed[32];
01359 
01360             buf = RNA_property_string_get_alloc(ptr, prop, buf_fixed, sizeof(buf_fixed), &buf_len);
01361 #ifdef USE_STRING_COERCE
01362             /* only file paths get special treatment, they may contain non utf-8 chars */
01363             if (subtype == PROP_BYTESTRING) {
01364                 ret = PyBytes_FromStringAndSize(buf, buf_len);
01365             }
01366             else if (ELEM3(subtype, PROP_FILEPATH, PROP_DIRPATH, PROP_FILENAME)) {
01367                 ret = PyC_UnicodeFromByteAndSize(buf, buf_len);
01368             }
01369             else {
01370                 ret = PyUnicode_FromStringAndSize(buf, buf_len);
01371             }
01372 #else // USE_STRING_COERCE
01373             if (subtype == PROP_BYTESTRING) {
01374                 ret = PyBytes_FromStringAndSize(buf, buf_len);
01375             }
01376             else {
01377                 ret = PyUnicode_FromStringAndSize(buf, buf_len);
01378             }
01379 #endif // USE_STRING_COERCE
01380             if (buf_fixed != buf) {
01381                 MEM_freeN((void *)buf);
01382             }
01383             break;
01384         }
01385         case PROP_ENUM:
01386         {
01387             ret = pyrna_enum_to_py(ptr, prop, RNA_property_enum_get(ptr, prop));
01388             break;
01389         }
01390         case PROP_POINTER:
01391         {
01392             PointerRNA newptr;
01393             newptr = RNA_property_pointer_get(ptr, prop);
01394             if (newptr.data) {
01395                 ret = pyrna_struct_CreatePyObject(&newptr);
01396             }
01397             else {
01398                 ret = Py_None;
01399                 Py_INCREF(ret);
01400             }
01401             break;
01402         }
01403         case PROP_COLLECTION:
01404             ret = pyrna_prop_CreatePyObject(ptr, prop);
01405             break;
01406         default:
01407             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
01408                          "bpy_struct internal error: unknown type '%d' (pyrna_prop_to_py)", type);
01409             ret = NULL;
01410             break;
01411     }
01412 
01413     return ret;
01414 }

01416 /* This function is used by operators and converting dicts into collections.
01417  * Its takes keyword args and fills them with property values */
01418 int pyrna_pydict_to_props(PointerRNA *ptr, PyObject *kw, int all_args, const char *error_prefix)
01419 {
01420     int error_val = 0;
01421     int totkw;
01422     const char *arg_name = NULL;
01423     PyObject *item;
01424 
01425     totkw = kw ? PyDict_Size(kw) : 0;
01426 
01427     RNA_STRUCT_BEGIN(ptr, prop) {
01428         arg_name = RNA_property_identifier(prop);
01429 
01430         if (strcmp(arg_name, "rna_type") == 0) continue;
01431 
01432         if (kw == NULL) {
01433             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
01434                          "%.200s: no keywords, expected \"%.200s\"",
01435                          error_prefix, arg_name ? arg_name : "<UNKNOWN>");
01436             error_val = -1;
01437             break;
01438         }
01439 
01440         item = PyDict_GetItemString(kw, arg_name); /* wont set an error */
01441 
01442         if (item == NULL) {
01443             if (all_args) {
01444                 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
01445                              "%.200s: keyword \"%.200s\" missing",
01446                              error_prefix, arg_name ? arg_name : "<UNKNOWN>");
01447                 error_val = -1; /* pyrna_py_to_prop sets the error */
01448                 break;
01449             }
01450         }
01451         else {
01452             if (pyrna_py_to_prop(ptr, prop, NULL, item, error_prefix)) {
01453                 error_val = -1;
01454                 break;
01455             }
01456             totkw--;
01457         }
01458     }
01459     RNA_STRUCT_END;
01460 
01461     if (error_val == 0 && totkw > 0) { /* some keywords were given that were not used :/ */
01462         PyObject *key, *value;
01463         Py_ssize_t pos = 0;
01464 
01465         while (PyDict_Next(kw, &pos, &key, &value)) {
01466             arg_name = _PyUnicode_AsString(key);
01467             if (RNA_struct_find_property(ptr, arg_name) == NULL) break;
01468             arg_name = NULL;
01469         }
01470 
01471         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
01472                      "%.200s: keyword \"%.200s\" unrecognized",
01473                      error_prefix, arg_name ? arg_name : "<UNKNOWN>");
01474         error_val = -1;
01475     }
01476 
01477     return error_val;
01478 }

01490 static int pyrna_py_to_prop(PointerRNA *ptr, PropertyRNA *prop, void *data, PyObject *value, const char *error_prefix)
01491 {
01492     /* XXX hard limits should be checked here */
01493     const int type = RNA_property_type(prop);
01494 
01495 
01496     if (RNA_property_array_check(prop)) {
01497         /* done getting the length */
01498         if (pyrna_py_to_array(ptr, prop, data, value, error_prefix) == -1) {
01499             return -1;
01500         }
01501     }
01502     else {
01503         /* Normal Property (not an array) */
01504 
01505         /* see if we can coorce into a python type - PropertyType */
01506         switch (type) {
01507             case PROP_BOOLEAN:
01508             {
01509                 int param;
01510                 /* prefer not to have an exception here
01511                  * however so many poll functions return None or a valid Object.
01512                  * its a hassle to convert these into a bool before returning, */
01513                 if (RNA_property_flag(prop) & PROP_OUTPUT)
01514                     param = PyObject_IsTrue(value);
01515                 else
01516                     param = PyLong_AsLong(value);
01517 
01518                 if (param < 0) {
01519                     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
01520                                  "%.200s %.200s.%.200s expected True/False or 0/1, not %.200s",
01521                                  error_prefix, RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type),
01522                                  RNA_property_identifier(prop), Py_TYPE(value)->tp_name);
01523                     return -1;
01524                 }
01525                 else {
01526                     if (data) *((int *)data) = param;
01527                     else RNA_property_boolean_set(ptr, prop, param);
01528                 }
01529                 break;
01530             }
01531             case PROP_INT:
01532             {
01533                 int overflow;
01534                 long param = PyLong_AsLongAndOverflow(value, &overflow);
01535                 if (overflow || (param > INT_MAX) || (param < INT_MIN)) {
01536                     PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
01537                                  "%.200s %.200s.%.200s value not in 'int' range "
01538                                  "(" STRINGIFY(INT_MIN) ", " STRINGIFY(INT_MAX) ")",
01539                                  error_prefix, RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type),
01540                                  RNA_property_identifier(prop));
01541                     return -1;
01542                 }
01543                 else if (param == -1 && PyErr_Occurred()) {
01544                     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
01545                                  "%.200s %.200s.%.200s expected an int type, not %.200s",
01546                                  error_prefix, RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type),
01547                                  RNA_property_identifier(prop), Py_TYPE(value)->tp_name);
01548                     return -1;
01549                 }
01550                 else {
01551                     int param_i = (int)param;
01552                     RNA_property_int_clamp(ptr, prop, &param_i);
01553                     if (data) *((int *)data) = param_i;
01554                     else RNA_property_int_set(ptr, prop, param_i);
01555                 }
01556                 break;
01557             }
01558             case PROP_FLOAT:
01559             {
01560                 float param = PyFloat_AsDouble(value);
01561                 if (PyErr_Occurred()) {
01562                     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
01563                                  "%.200s %.200s.%.200s expected a float type, not %.200s",
01564                                  error_prefix, RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type),
01565                                  RNA_property_identifier(prop), Py_TYPE(value)->tp_name);
01566                     return -1;
01567                 }
01568                 else {
01569                     RNA_property_float_clamp(ptr, prop, (float *)&param);
01570                     if (data) *((float *)data) = param;
01571                     else RNA_property_float_set(ptr, prop, param);
01572                 }
01573                 break;
01574             }
01575             case PROP_STRING:
01576             {
01577                 const int subtype = RNA_property_subtype(prop);
01578                 const char *param;
01579 
01580                 if (subtype == PROP_BYTESTRING) {
01581 
01582                     /* Byte String */
01583 
01584                     param = PyBytes_AsString(value);
01585 
01586                     if (param == NULL) {
01587                         if (PyBytes_Check(value)) {
01588                             /* there was an error assigning a string type,
01589                              * rather than setting a new error, prefix the existing one
01590                              */
01591                             PyC_Err_Format_Prefix(PyExc_TypeError,
01592                                                   "%.200s %.200s.%.200s error assigning bytes",
01593                                                   error_prefix, RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type),
01594                                                   RNA_property_identifier(prop));
01595                         }
01596                         else {
01597                             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
01598                                          "%.200s %.200s.%.200s expected a bytes type, not %.200s",
01599                                          error_prefix, RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type),
01600                                          RNA_property_identifier(prop), Py_TYPE(value)->tp_name);
01601                         }
01602 
01603                         return -1;
01604                     }
01605                     else {
01606                         /* same as unicode */
01607                         if (data) *((char **)data) = (char *)param;  /*XXX, this is suspect but needed for function calls, need to see if theres a better way */
01608                         else RNA_property_string_set(ptr, prop, param);
01609                     }
01610                 }
01611                 else {
01612 
01613                     /* Unicode String */
01614 
01615 #ifdef USE_STRING_COERCE
01616                     PyObject *value_coerce = NULL;
01617                     if (ELEM3(subtype, PROP_FILEPATH, PROP_DIRPATH, PROP_FILENAME)) {
01618                         /* TODO, get size */
01619                         param = PyC_UnicodeAsByte(value, &value_coerce);
01620                     }
01621                     else {
01622                         param = _PyUnicode_AsString(value);
01623 #ifdef WITH_INTERNATIONAL
01624                         if (subtype == PROP_TRANSLATE) {
01625                             param = IFACE_(param);
01626                         }
01627 #endif // WITH_INTERNATIONAL
01628 
01629                     }
01630 #else // USE_STRING_COERCE
01631                     param = _PyUnicode_AsString(value);
01632 #endif // USE_STRING_COERCE
01633 
01634                     if (param == NULL) {
01635                         if (PyUnicode_Check(value)) {
01636                             /* there was an error assigning a string type,
01637                              * rather than setting a new error, prefix the existing one
01638                              */
01639                             PyC_Err_Format_Prefix(PyExc_TypeError,
01640                                                   "%.200s %.200s.%.200s error assigning string",
01641                                                   error_prefix, RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type),
01642                                                   RNA_property_identifier(prop));
01643                         }
01644                         else {
01645                             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
01646                                          "%.200s %.200s.%.200s expected a string type, not %.200s",
01647                                          error_prefix, RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type),
01648                                          RNA_property_identifier(prop), Py_TYPE(value)->tp_name);
01649                         }
01650 
01651                         return -1;
01652                     }
01653                     else {
01654                         /* same as bytes */
01655                         if (data) *((char **)data) = (char *)param;  /*XXX, this is suspect but needed for function calls, need to see if theres a better way */
01656                         else RNA_property_string_set(ptr, prop, param);
01657                     }
01658 #ifdef USE_STRING_COERCE
01659                     Py_XDECREF(value_coerce);
01660 #endif // USE_STRING_COERCE
01661                 }
01662                 break;
01663             }
01664             case PROP_ENUM:
01665             {
01666                 int val = 0;
01667 
01668                 /* type checkins is done by each function */
01669                 if (RNA_property_flag(prop) & PROP_ENUM_FLAG) {
01670                     /* set of enum items, concatenate all values with OR */
01671                     if (pyrna_prop_to_enum_bitfield(ptr, prop, value, &val, error_prefix) < 0) {
01672                         return -1;
01673                     }
01674                 }
01675                 else {
01676                     /* simple enum string */
01677                     if (pyrna_string_to_enum(value, ptr, prop, &val, error_prefix) < 0) {
01678                         return -1;
01679                     }
01680                 }
01681 
01682                 if (data) *((int *)data) = val;
01683                 else RNA_property_enum_set(ptr, prop, val);
01684 
01685                 break;
01686             }
01687             case PROP_POINTER:
01688             {
01689                 PyObject *value_new = NULL;
01690 
01691                 StructRNA *ptr_type = RNA_property_pointer_type(ptr, prop);
01692                 int flag = RNA_property_flag(prop);
01693 
01694                 /* this is really nasty!, so we can fake the operator having direct properties eg:
01695                  * layout.prop(self, "filepath")
01696                  * ... which infact should be
01697                  * layout.prop(self.properties, "filepath")
01698                  *
01699                  * we need to do this trick.
01700                  * if the prop is not an operator type and the pyobject is an operator,
01701                  * use its properties in place of its self.
01702                  *
01703                  * this is so bad that its almost a good reason to do away with fake 'self.properties -> self' class mixing
01704                  * if this causes problems in the future it should be removed.
01705                  */
01706                 if ((ptr_type == &RNA_AnyType) &&
01707                     (BPy_StructRNA_Check(value)) &&
01708                     (RNA_struct_is_a(((BPy_StructRNA *)value)->ptr.type, &RNA_Operator)))
01709                 {
01710                     value = PyObject_GetAttrString(value, "properties");
01711                     value_new = value;
01712                 }
01713 
01714 
01715                 /* if property is an OperatorProperties pointer and value is a map,
01716                  * forward back to pyrna_pydict_to_props */
01717                 if (RNA_struct_is_a(ptr_type, &RNA_OperatorProperties) && PyDict_Check(value)) {
01718                     PointerRNA opptr = RNA_property_pointer_get(ptr, prop);
01719                     return pyrna_pydict_to_props(&opptr, value, 0, error_prefix);
01720                 }
01721 
01722                 /* another exception, allow to pass a collection as an RNA property */
01723                 if (Py_TYPE(value) == &pyrna_prop_collection_Type) { /* ok to ignore idprop collections */
01724                     PointerRNA c_ptr;
01725                     BPy_PropertyRNA *value_prop = (BPy_PropertyRNA *)value;
01726                     if (RNA_property_collection_type_get(&value_prop->ptr, value_prop->prop, &c_ptr)) {
01727                         value = pyrna_struct_CreatePyObject(&c_ptr);
01728                         value_new = value;
01729                     }
01730                     else {
01731                         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
01732                                      "%.200s %.200s.%.200s collection has no type, "
01733                                      "cant be used as a %.200s type",
01734                                      error_prefix, RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type),
01735                                      RNA_property_identifier(prop), RNA_struct_identifier(ptr_type));
01736                         return -1;
01737                     }
01738                 }
01739 
01740                 if (!BPy_StructRNA_Check(value) && value != Py_None) {
01741                     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
01742                                  "%.200s %.200s.%.200s expected a %.200s type, not %.200s",
01743                                  error_prefix, RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type),
01744                                  RNA_property_identifier(prop), RNA_struct_identifier(ptr_type),
01745                                  Py_TYPE(value)->tp_name);
01746                     Py_XDECREF(value_new); return -1;
01747                 }
01748                 else if ((flag & PROP_NEVER_NULL) && value == Py_None) {
01749                     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
01750                                  "%.200s %.200s.%.200s does not support a 'None' assignment %.200s type",
01751                                  error_prefix, RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type),
01752                                  RNA_property_identifier(prop), RNA_struct_identifier(ptr_type));
01753                     Py_XDECREF(value_new); return -1;
01754                 }
01755                 else if ((value != Py_None) &&
01756                          ((flag & PROP_ID_SELF_CHECK) && ptr->id.data == ((BPy_StructRNA *)value)->ptr.id.data))
01757                 {
01758                     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
01759                                  "%.200s %.200s.%.200s ID type does not support assignment to its self",
01760                                  error_prefix, RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type),
01761                                  RNA_property_identifier(prop));
01762                     Py_XDECREF(value_new); return -1;
01763                 }
01764                 else {
01765                     BPy_StructRNA *param = (BPy_StructRNA *)value;
01766                     int raise_error = FALSE;
01767                     if (data) {
01768 
01769                         if (flag & PROP_RNAPTR) {
01770                             if (value == Py_None)
01771                                 memset(data, 0, sizeof(PointerRNA));
01772                             else
01773                                 *((PointerRNA *)data) = param->ptr;
01774                         }
01775                         else if (value == Py_None) {
01776                             *((void **)data) = NULL;
01777                         }
01778                         else if (RNA_struct_is_a(param->ptr.type, ptr_type)) {
01779                             *((void **)data) = param->ptr.data;
01780                         }
01781                         else {
01782                             raise_error = TRUE;
01783                         }
01784                     }
01785                     else {
01786                         /* data == NULL, assign to RNA */
01787                         if (value == Py_None) {
01788                             PointerRNA valueptr = {{NULL}};
01789                             RNA_property_pointer_set(ptr, prop, valueptr);
01790                         }
01791                         else if (RNA_struct_is_a(param->ptr.type, ptr_type)) {
01792                             RNA_property_pointer_set(ptr, prop, param->ptr);
01793                         }
01794                         else {
01795                             PointerRNA tmp;
01796                             RNA_pointer_create(NULL, ptr_type, NULL, &tmp);
01797                             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
01798                                          "%.200s %.200s.%.200s expected a %.200s type. not %.200s",
01799                                          error_prefix, RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type),
01800                                          RNA_property_identifier(prop), RNA_struct_identifier(tmp.type),
01801                                          RNA_struct_identifier(param->ptr.type));
01802                             Py_XDECREF(value_new); return -1;
01803                         }
01804                     }
01805 
01806                     if (raise_error) {
01807                         PointerRNA tmp;
01808                         RNA_pointer_create(NULL, ptr_type, NULL, &tmp);
01809                         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
01810                                      "%.200s %.200s.%.200s expected a %.200s type, not %.200s",
01811                                      error_prefix, RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type),
01812                                      RNA_property_identifier(prop), RNA_struct_identifier(tmp.type),
01813                                      RNA_struct_identifier(param->ptr.type));
01814                         Py_XDECREF(value_new); return -1;
01815                     }
01816                 }

01859                                      RNA_property_identifier(prop), Py_TYPE(item)->tp_name);
01860                         Py_XDECREF(item);
01861                         return -1;
01862                     }

01880                                      RNA_property_identifier(prop), msg_char);
01881

01883                         Py_DECREF(msg);

01890             }

01893                              "%.200s %.200s.%.200s unknown property type (pyrna_py_to_prop)",
01894                              error_prefix, RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type),

01915 static int pyrna_py_to_prop_array_index(BPy_PropertyArrayRNA *self, int index, PyObject *value)
01916 {
01917     int ret = 0;
01918     PointerRNA *ptr = &self->ptr;
01919     PropertyRNA *prop = self->prop;
01920 
01921     const int totdim = RNA_property_array_dimension(ptr, prop, NULL);
01922

01926             /* error is set */

01928         }
01929     }
01930     else {
01931         /* see if we can coerce into a python type - PropertyType */
01932         switch (RNA_property_type(prop)) {

01980     if (RNA_property_update_check(prop)) {

02136  * also for:     bpy.data.objects.get(("some_id_name", "//some_lib_name.blend"), fallback)
02137  *
02138  * note:
02139  * error codes since this is not to be called directly from python,
02140  * this matches pythons __contains__ values capi.

02144 int pyrna_prop_collection_subscript_str_lib_pair_ptr(BPy_PropertyRNA *self, PyObject *key,
02145                                                      const char *err_prefix, const short err_not_found,
02146                                                      PointerRNA *r_ptr
02147                                                      )
02148 {
02149     char *keyname;
02150 
02151     /* first validate the args, all we know is that they are a tuple */
02152     if (PyTuple_GET_SIZE(key) != 2) {
02153         PyErr_Format(PyExc_KeyError,
02154                      "%s: tuple key must be a pair, not size %d",
02155                      err_prefix, PyTuple_GET_SIZE(key));
02156         return -1;
02157     }
02158     else if (self->ptr.type != &RNA_BlendData) {
02159         PyErr_Format(PyExc_KeyError,
02160                      "%s: is only valid for bpy.data collections, not %.200s",
02161                      err_prefix, RNA_struct_identifier(self->ptr.type));
02162         return -1;
02163     }
02164     else if ((keyname = _PyUnicode_AsString(PyTuple_GET_ITEM(key, 0))) == NULL) {
02165         PyErr_Format(PyExc_KeyError,
02166                      "%s: id must be a string, not %.200s",
02167                      err_prefix, Py_TYPE(PyTuple_GET_ITEM(key, 0))->tp_name);
02168         return -1;
02169     }
02170     else {
02171         PyObject *keylib = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(key, 1);
02172         Library *lib;
02173         int found = FALSE;
02174 
02175         if (keylib == Py_None) {
02176             lib = NULL;
02177         }
02178         else if (PyUnicode_Check(keylib)) {
02179             Main *bmain = self->ptr.data;
02180             const char *keylib_str = _PyUnicode_AsString(keylib);
02181             lib = BLI_findstring(&bmain->library, keylib_str, offsetof(Library, name));
02182             if (lib == NULL) {
02183                 if (err_not_found) {
02184                     PyErr_Format(PyExc_KeyError,
02185                                  "%s: lib name '%.240s' "
02186                                  "does not reference a valid library",
02187                                  err_prefix, keylib_str);
02188                     return -1;
02189                 }
02190                 else {
02191                     return 0;
02192                 }
02193 
02194             }
02195         }
02196         else {
02197             PyErr_Format(PyExc_KeyError,
02198                          "%s: lib must be a sting or None, not %.200s",
02199                          err_prefix, Py_TYPE(keylib)->tp_name);
02200             return -1;
02201         }
02202 
02203         /* lib is either a valid poniter or NULL,
02204          * either way can do direct comparison with id.lib */
02205 
02206         RNA_PROP_BEGIN(&self->ptr, itemptr, self->prop) {
02207             ID *id = itemptr.data; /* always an ID */
02208             if (id->lib == lib && (strncmp(keyname, id->name + 2, sizeof(id->name) - 2) == 0)) {
02209                 found = TRUE;
02210                 if (r_ptr) {
02211                     *r_ptr = itemptr;
02212                 }
02213                 break;
02214             }
02215         }
02216         RNA_PROP_END;
02217 
02218         /* we may want to fail silently as with collection.get() */
02219         if ((found == FALSE) && err_not_found) {
02220             /* only runs for getitem access so use fixed string */
02221             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_KeyError,
02222                             "bpy_prop_collection[key, lib]: not found");

02372 static PyObject *pyrna_prop_collection_subscript(BPy_PropertyRNA *self, PyObject *key)
02373 {
02374     PYRNA_PROP_CHECK_OBJ(self);
02375 
02376     if (PyUnicode_Check(key)) {
02377         return pyrna_prop_collection_subscript_str(self, _PyUnicode_AsString(key));
02378     }
02379     else if (PyIndex_Check(key)) {
02380         Py_ssize_t i = PyNumber_AsSsize_t(key, PyExc_IndexError);
02381         if (i == -1 && PyErr_Occurred())
02382             return NULL;
02383 
02384         return pyrna_prop_collection_subscript_int(self, i);
02385     }
02386     else if (PySlice_Check(key)) {
02387         PySliceObject *key_slice = (PySliceObject *)key;
02388         Py_ssize_t step = 1;
02389 
02390         if (key_slice->step != Py_None && !_PyEval_SliceIndex(key, &step)) {
02391             return NULL;
02392         }
02393         else if (step != 1) {
02394             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "bpy_prop_collection[slice]: slice steps not supported");
02395             return NULL;
02396         }
02397         else if (key_slice->start == Py_None && key_slice->stop == Py_None) {
02398             return pyrna_prop_collection_subscript_slice(self, 0, PY_SSIZE_T_MAX);
02399         }
02400         else {
02401             Py_ssize_t start = 0, stop = PY_SSIZE_T_MAX;
02402 
02403             /* avoid PySlice_GetIndicesEx because it needs to know the length ahead of time. */
02404             if (key_slice->start != Py_None && !_PyEval_SliceIndex(key_slice->start, &start)) return NULL;
02405             if (key_slice->stop  != Py_None && !_PyEval_SliceIndex(key_slice->stop,  &stop))  return NULL;
02406 
02407             if (start < 0 || stop < 0) {
02408                 /* only get the length for negative values */
02409                 Py_ssize_t len = (Py_ssize_t)RNA_property_collection_length(&self->ptr, self->prop);
02410                 if (start < 0) start += len;
02411                 if (stop < 0) start += len;
02412             }
02413 
02414             if (stop - start <= 0) {
02415                 return PyList_New(0);
02416             }
02417             else {
02418                 return pyrna_prop_collection_subscript_slice(self, start, stop);
02419             }
02420         }
02421     }
02422     else if (PyTuple_Check(key)) {
02423         /* special case, for ID datablocks we */
02424         return pyrna_prop_collection_subscript_str_lib_pair(self, key,

02436 /* generic check to see if a PyObject is compatible with a collection
02437  * -1 on failure, 0 on success, sets the error */
02438 static int pyrna_prop_collection_type_check(BPy_PropertyRNA *self, PyObject *value)
02439 {
02440     StructRNA *prop_srna;
02441 
02442     if (value == Py_None) {
02443         if (RNA_property_flag(self->prop) & PROP_NEVER_NULL) {
02444             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
02445                          "bpy_prop_collection[key] = value: invalid, "
02446                          "this collection doesn't support None assignment");
02447             return -1;
02448         }
02449         else {
02450             return 0; /* None is OK */
02451         }
02452     }
02453     else if (BPy_StructRNA_Check(value) == 0) {
02454         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
02455                      "bpy_prop_collection[key] = value: invalid, "
02456                      "expected a StructRNA type or None, not a %.200s",
02457                      Py_TYPE(value)->tp_name);
02458         return -1;
02459     }
02460     else if ((prop_srna = RNA_property_pointer_type(&self->ptr, self->prop))) {
02461         StructRNA *value_srna = ((BPy_StructRNA *)value)->ptr.type;
02462         if (RNA_struct_is_a(value_srna, prop_srna) == 0) {
02463             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
02464                          "bpy_prop_collection[key] = value: invalid, "
02465                          "expected a '%.200s' type or None, not a '%.200s'",
02466                          RNA_struct_identifier(prop_srna),
02467                          RNA_struct_identifier(value_srna)
02468                          );
02469             return -1;
02470         }
02471         else {
02472             return 0; /* OK, this is the correct type!*/
02473         }
02474     }
02475 
02476     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
02477                  "bpy_prop_collection[key] = value: internal error, "
02478                  "failed to get the collection type");
02479     return -1;
02480 }

02612 /* could call (pyrna_py_to_prop_array_index(self, i, value) in a loop but it is slow */
02613 static int prop_subscript_ass_array_slice(PointerRNA *ptr, PropertyRNA *prop,
02614                                           int start, int stop, int length, PyObject *value_orig)
02615 {
02616     PyObject *value;
02617     int count;
02618     void *values_alloc = NULL;
02619     int ret = 0;
02620 
02621     if (value_orig == NULL) {
02622         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
02623                         "bpy_prop_array[slice] = value: deleting with list types is not supported by bpy_struct");
02624         return -1;
02625     }
02626 
02627     if (!(value = PySequence_Fast(value_orig, "bpy_prop_array[slice] = value: assignment is not a sequence type"))) {
02628         return -1;
02629     }
02630 
02631     if (PySequence_Fast_GET_SIZE(value) != stop - start) {
02632         Py_DECREF(value);
02633         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
02634                         "bpy_prop_array[slice] = value: re-sizing bpy_struct arrays isn't supported");
02635         return -1;
02636     }
02637 
02638     switch (RNA_property_type(prop)) {
02639         case PROP_FLOAT:
02640         {
02641             float values_stack[PYRNA_STACK_ARRAY];
02642             float *values, fval;
02643 
02644             float min, max;
02645             RNA_property_float_range(ptr, prop, &min, &max);
02646 
02647             if (length > PYRNA_STACK_ARRAY) { values = values_alloc = PyMem_MALLOC(sizeof(float) * length); }
02648             else                            { values = values_stack; }
02649             if (start != 0 || stop != length) /* partial assignment? - need to get the array */
02650                 RNA_property_float_get_array(ptr, prop, values);
02651 
02652             for (count = start; count < stop; count++) {
02653                 fval = PyFloat_AsDouble(PySequence_Fast_GET_ITEM(value, count - start));
02654                 CLAMP(fval, min, max);
02655                 values[count] = fval;
02656             }
02657 
02658             if (PyErr_Occurred()) ret = -1;
02659             else                  RNA_property_float_set_array(ptr, prop, values);
02660             break;
02661         }
02662         case PROP_BOOLEAN:
02663         {
02664             int values_stack[PYRNA_STACK_ARRAY];
02665             int *values;
02666             if (length > PYRNA_STACK_ARRAY) { values = values_alloc = PyMem_MALLOC(sizeof(int) * length); }
02667             else                            { values = values_stack; }
02668 
02669             if (start != 0 || stop != length) /* partial assignment? - need to get the array */
02670                 RNA_property_boolean_get_array(ptr, prop, values);
02671 
02672             for (count = start; count < stop; count++)
02673                 values[count] = PyLong_AsLong(PySequence_Fast_GET_ITEM(value, count - start));
02674 
02675             if (PyErr_Occurred()) ret = -1;
02676             else                  RNA_property_boolean_set_array(ptr, prop, values);
02677             break;
02678         }
02679         case PROP_INT:
02680         {
02681             int values_stack[PYRNA_STACK_ARRAY];
02682             int *values, ival;
02683 
02684             int min, max;
02685             RNA_property_int_range(ptr, prop, &min, &max);
02686 
02687             if (length > PYRNA_STACK_ARRAY) { values = values_alloc = PyMem_MALLOC(sizeof(int) * length); }
02688             else                            { values = values_stack; }
02689 
02690             if (start != 0 || stop != length) /* partial assignment? - need to get the array */
02691                 RNA_property_int_get_array(ptr, prop, values);
02692 
02693             for (count = start; count < stop; count++) {
02694                 ival = PyLong_AsLong(PySequence_Fast_GET_ITEM(value, count - start));
02695                 CLAMP(ival, min, max);
02696                 values[count] = ival;
02697             }
02698 
02699             if (PyErr_Occurred()) ret = -1;
02700             else                  RNA_property_int_set_array(ptr, prop, values);
02701             break;
02702         }
02703         default:
02704             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "not an array type");
02705             ret = -1;
02706     }
02707 
02708     Py_DECREF(value);
02709 
02710     if (values_alloc) {
02711         PyMem_FREE(values_alloc);
02712     }
02713 
02714     return ret;
02715 
02716 }

02736 static int pyrna_prop_array_ass_subscript(BPy_PropertyArrayRNA *self, PyObject *key, PyObject *value)
02737 {
02738     /* char *keyname = NULL; */ /* not supported yet */
02739     int ret = -1;
02740 
02741     PYRNA_PROP_CHECK_INT((BPy_PropertyRNA *)self);
02742 
02743     if (!RNA_property_editable_flag(&self->ptr, self->prop)) {
02744         PyErr_Format(PyExc_AttributeError,
02745                      "bpy_prop_collection: attribute \"%.200s\" from \"%.200s\" is read-only",
02746                      RNA_property_identifier(self->prop), RNA_struct_identifier(self->ptr.type));
02747         ret = -1;
02748     }
02749 
02750     else if (PyIndex_Check(key)) {
02751         Py_ssize_t i = PyNumber_AsSsize_t(key, PyExc_IndexError);
02752         if (i == -1 && PyErr_Occurred()) {
02753             ret = -1;
02754         }
02755         else {
02756             ret = prop_subscript_ass_array_int(self, i, value);
02757         }
02758     }
02759     else if (PySlice_Check(key)) {
02760         int len = RNA_property_array_length(&self->ptr, self->prop);
02761         Py_ssize_t start, stop, step, slicelength;
02762 
02763         if (PySlice_GetIndicesEx((void *)key, len, &start, &stop, &step, &slicelength) < 0) {
02764             ret = -1;
02765         }
02766         else if (slicelength <= 0) {
02767             ret = 0; /* do nothing */
02768         }
02769         else if (step == 1) {
02770             ret = prop_subscript_ass_array_slice(&self->ptr, self->prop, start, stop, len, value);
02771         }
02772         else {
02773             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "slice steps not supported with rna");
02774             ret = -1;
02775         }
02776     }
02777     else {
02778         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_AttributeError, "invalid key, key must be an int");
02779         ret = -1;
02780     }
02781 
02782     if (ret != -1) {
02783         if (RNA_property_update_check(self->prop)) {
02784             RNA_property_update(BPy_GetContext(), &self->ptr, self->prop);
02785         }
02786     }
02787 
02788     return ret;
02789 }

02929     IDProperty *group, *idprop;

03430 //---------------getattr--------------------------------------------
03431 static PyObject *pyrna_struct_getattro(BPy_StructRNA *self, PyObject *pyname)
03432 {
03433     const char *name = _PyUnicode_AsString(pyname);
03434     PyObject *ret;
03435     PropertyRNA *prop;
03436     FunctionRNA *func;
03437 
03438     PYRNA_STRUCT_CHECK_OBJ(self);
03439 
03440     if (name == NULL) {
03441         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_AttributeError, "bpy_struct: __getattr__ must be a string");
03442         ret = NULL;
03443     }
03444     else if (name[0] == '_') { // rna can't start with a "_", so for __dict__ and similar we can skip using rna lookups
03445         /* annoying exception, maybe we need to have different types for this... */
03446         if ((strcmp(name, "__getitem__") == 0 || strcmp(name, "__setitem__") == 0) && !RNA_struct_idprops_check(self->ptr.type)) {
03447             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_AttributeError, "bpy_struct: no __getitem__ support for this type");
03448             ret = NULL;
03449         }
03450         else {
03451             ret = PyObject_GenericGetAttr((PyObject *)self, pyname);
03452         }
03453     }
03454     else if ((prop = RNA_struct_find_property(&self->ptr, name))) {
03455         ret = pyrna_prop_to_py(&self->ptr, prop);
03456     }
03457     /* RNA function only if callback is declared (no optional functions) */
03458     else if ((func = RNA_struct_find_function(&self->ptr, name)) && RNA_function_defined(func)) {
03459         ret = pyrna_func_to_py(&self->ptr, func);
03460     }
03461     else if (self->ptr.type == &RNA_Context) {
03462         bContext *C = self->ptr.data;
03463         if (C == NULL) {
03464             PyErr_Format(PyExc_AttributeError,
03465                          "bpy_struct: Context is 'NULL', can't get \"%.200s\" from context",
03466                          name);
03467             ret = NULL;
03468         }
03469         else {
03470             PointerRNA newptr;
03471             ListBase newlb;
03472             short newtype;
03473 
03474             int done = CTX_data_get(C, name, &newptr, &newlb, &newtype);
03475 
03476             if (done == 1) { /* found */
03477                 switch (newtype) {
03478                     case CTX_DATA_TYPE_POINTER:
03479                         if (newptr.data == NULL) {
03480                             ret = Py_None;
03481                             Py_INCREF(ret);
03482                         }
03483                         else {
03484                             ret = pyrna_struct_CreatePyObject(&newptr);
03485                         }
03486                         break;
03487                     case CTX_DATA_TYPE_COLLECTION:
03488                     {
03489                         CollectionPointerLink *link;
03490                         PyObject *linkptr;
03491 
03492                         ret = PyList_New(0);
03493 
03494                         for (link = newlb.first; link; link = link->next) {
03495                             linkptr = pyrna_struct_CreatePyObject(&link->ptr);
03496                             PyList_Append(ret, linkptr);
03497                             Py_DECREF(linkptr);
03498                         }
03499                     }
03500                     break;
03501                     default:
03502                         /* should never happen */
03503                         BLI_assert(!"Invalid context type");
03504 
03505                         PyErr_Format(PyExc_AttributeError,
03506                                      "bpy_struct: Context type invalid %d, can't get \"%.200s\" from context",
03507                                      newtype, name);
03508                         ret = NULL;
03509                 }
03510             }
03511             else if (done == -1) { /* found but not set */
03512                 ret = Py_None;
03513                 Py_INCREF(ret);
03514             }
03515             else { /* not found in the context */
03516                 /* lookup the subclass. raise an error if its not found */
03517                 ret = PyObject_GenericGetAttr((PyObject *)self, pyname);
03518             }
03519 
03520             BLI_freelistN(&newlb);
03521         }
03522     }
03523     else {
03524 #if 0
03525         PyErr_Format(PyExc_AttributeError,
03526                      "bpy_struct: attribute \"%.200s\" not found",
03527                      name);
03528         ret = NULL;
03529 #endif
03530         /* Include this in case this instance is a subtype of a python class
03531          * In these instances we may want to return a function or variable provided by the subtype
03532          *
03533          * Also needed to return methods when its not a subtype
03534          * */
03535 
03536         /* The error raised here will be displayed */
03537         ret = PyObject_GenericGetAttr((PyObject *)self, pyname);
03538     }
03539 
03540     return ret;
03541 }

03626             int ret = deferred_register_prop(srna, attr, value);
03627             if (ret == -1) {
03628                 /* error set */
03629                 return ret;
03630             }
03631 
03632             /* pass through and assign to the classes __dict__ as well
03633              * when the value isn't assigned it still creates the RNA property
03634              * but gets confusing from script writers POV if the assigned value cant be read back. */
03635         }
03636         else {
03637             /* remove existing property if its set or we also end up with confusion */
03638             RNA_def_property_free_identifier(srna, attr_str); /* ignore on failure */
03639         }
03640     }
03641     else { /* __delattr__ */
03642         /* first find if this is a registered property */
03643         const int ret = RNA_def_property_free_identifier(srna, attr_str);
03644         if (ret == -1) {
03645             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
03646                          "struct_meta_idprop.detattr(): '%s' not a dynamic property",
03647                          attr_str);
03648             return -1;
03649         }
03650     }
03651 
03652     /* fallback to standard py, delattr/setattr */
03653     return PyType_Type.tp_setattro(cls, attr, value);
03654 }

03656 static int pyrna_struct_setattro(BPy_StructRNA *self, PyObject *pyname, PyObject *value)
03657 {
03658     const char *name = _PyUnicode_AsString(pyname);
03659     PropertyRNA *prop = NULL;
03660 
03661     PYRNA_STRUCT_CHECK_INT(self);
03662 
03663 #ifdef USE_PEDANTIC_WRITE
03664     if (rna_disallow_writes && rna_id_write_error(&self->ptr, pyname)) {
03665         return -1;
03666     }
03667 #endif // USE_PEDANTIC_WRITE
03668 
03669     if (name == NULL) {
03670         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_AttributeError, "bpy_struct: __setattr__ must be a string");
03671         return -1;
03672     }
03673     else if (name[0] != '_' && (prop = RNA_struct_find_property(&self->ptr, name))) {
03674         if (!RNA_property_editable_flag(&self->ptr, prop)) {
03675             PyErr_Format(PyExc_AttributeError,
03676                          "bpy_struct: attribute \"%.200s\" from \"%.200s\" is read-only",
03677                          RNA_property_identifier(prop), RNA_struct_identifier(self->ptr.type));
03678             return -1;
03679         }
03680     }
03681     else if (self->ptr.type == &RNA_Context) {
03682         /* code just raises correct error, context prop's cant be set, unless its apart of the py class */
03683         bContext *C = self->ptr.data;
03684         if (C == NULL) {
03685             PyErr_Format(PyExc_AttributeError,
03686                          "bpy_struct: Context is 'NULL', can't set \"%.200s\" from context",
03687                          name);
03688             return -1;
03689         }
03690         else {
03691             PointerRNA newptr;
03692             ListBase newlb;
03693             short newtype;
03694 
03695             int done = CTX_data_get(C, name, &newptr, &newlb, &newtype);
03696 
03697             if (done == 1) {
03698                 PyErr_Format(PyExc_AttributeError,
03699                              "bpy_struct: Context property \"%.200s\" is read-only",
03700                              name);
03701                 BLI_freelistN(&newlb);
03702                 return -1;
03703             }
03704 
03705             BLI_freelistN(&newlb);
03706         }
03707     }
03708 
03709     /* pyrna_py_to_prop sets its own exceptions */
03710     if (prop) {
03711         if (value == NULL) {
03712             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_AttributeError, "bpy_struct: del not supported");
03713             return -1;
03714         }
03715         return pyrna_py_to_prop(&self->ptr, prop, NULL, value, "bpy_struct: item.attr = val:");
03716     }
03717     else {
03718         return PyObject_GenericSetAttr((PyObject *)self, pyname, value);
03719     }
03720 }

04225         *raw_type = RNA_property_raw_type(prop);
04226         *attr_tot = RNA_property_array_length(&itemptr, prop);
04227         *attr_signed = (RNA_property_subtype(prop) == PROP_UNSIGNED) ? FALSE : TRUE;
04228         break;
04229     }
04230     RNA_PROP_END;
04231 }

04233 /* pyrna_prop_collection_foreach_get/set both use this */
04234 static int foreach_parse_args(BPy_PropertyRNA *self, PyObject *args,
04235 
04236                               /* values to assign */
04237                               const char **attr, PyObject **seq, int *tot, int *size,
04238                               RawPropertyType *raw_type, int *attr_tot, int *attr_signed
04239                               )
04240 {
04241 #if 0
04242     int array_tot;
04243     int target_tot;
04244 #endif
04245 
04246     *size = *attr_tot = *attr_signed = FALSE;
04247     *raw_type = PROP_RAW_UNSET;
04248 
04249     if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "sO", attr, seq) || (!PySequence_Check(*seq) && PyObject_CheckBuffer(*seq))) {
04250         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "foreach_get(attr, sequence) expects a string and a sequence");
04251         return -1;
04252     }
04253 
04254     *tot = PySequence_Size(*seq); // TODO - buffer may not be a sequence! array.array() is tho.
04255 
04256     if (*tot > 0) {
04257         foreach_attr_type(self, *attr, raw_type, attr_tot, attr_signed);
04258         *size = RNA_raw_type_sizeof(*raw_type);
04259 
04260 #if 0   // works fine but not strictly needed, we could allow RNA_property_collection_raw_* to do the checks
04261         if ((*attr_tot) < 1)
04262             *attr_tot = 1;
04263 
04264         if (RNA_property_type(self->prop) == PROP_COLLECTION)
04265             array_tot = RNA_property_collection_length(&self->ptr, self->prop);
04266         else
04267             array_tot = RNA_property_array_length(&self->ptr, self->prop);
04268 
04269 
04270         target_tot = array_tot * (*attr_tot);
04271 
04272         /* rna_access.c - rna_raw_access(...) uses this same method */
04273         if (target_tot != (*tot)) {
04274             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
04275                          "foreach_get(attr, sequence) sequence length mismatch given %d, needed %d",
04276                          *tot, target_tot);
04277             return -1;
04278         }
04279 #endif
04280     }
04281 
04282     /* check 'attr_tot' otherwise we don't know if any values were set
04283      * this isn't ideal because it means running on an empty list may fail silently when its not compatible. */
04284     if (*size == 0 && *attr_tot != 0) {
04285         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_AttributeError, "attribute does not support foreach method");
04286         return -1;
04287     }
04288     return 0;
04289 }

04291 static int foreach_compat_buffer(RawPropertyType raw_type, int attr_signed, const char *format)
04292 {
04293     char f = format ? *format : 'B'; /* B is assumed when not set */
04294 
04295     switch (raw_type) {
04296         case PROP_RAW_CHAR:
04297             if (attr_signed) return (f == 'b') ? 1 : 0;
04298             else             return (f == 'B') ? 1 : 0;
04299         case PROP_RAW_SHORT:
04300             if (attr_signed) return (f == 'h') ? 1 : 0;
04301             else             return (f == 'H') ? 1 : 0;
04302         case PROP_RAW_INT:
04303             if (attr_signed) return (f == 'i') ? 1 : 0;
04304             else             return (f == 'I') ? 1 : 0;
04305         case PROP_RAW_FLOAT:
04306             return (f == 'f') ? 1 : 0;
04307         case PROP_RAW_DOUBLE:
04308             return (f == 'd') ? 1 : 0;
04309         case PROP_RAW_UNSET:
04310             return 0;
04311     }
04312 
04313     return 0;
04314 }

04316 static PyObject *foreach_getset(BPy_PropertyRNA *self, PyObject *args, int set)
04317 {
04318     PyObject *item = NULL;
04319     int i = 0, ok = 0, buffer_is_compat;
04320     void *array = NULL;
04321 
04322     /* get/set both take the same args currently */
04323     const char *attr;
04324     PyObject *seq;
04325     int tot, size, attr_tot, attr_signed;
04326     RawPropertyType raw_type;
04327 
04328     if (foreach_parse_args(self, args, &attr, &seq, &tot, &size, &raw_type, &attr_tot, &attr_signed) < 0)
04329         return NULL;
04330 
04331     if (tot == 0)
04332         Py_RETURN_NONE;
04333 
04334 
04335 
04336     if (set) { /* get the array from python */
04337         buffer_is_compat = FALSE;
04338         if (PyObject_CheckBuffer(seq)) {
04339             Py_buffer buf;
04340             PyObject_GetBuffer(seq, &buf, PyBUF_SIMPLE | PyBUF_FORMAT);
04341 
04342             /* check if the buffer matches */
04343 
04344             buffer_is_compat = foreach_compat_buffer(raw_type, attr_signed, buf.format);
04345 
04346             if (buffer_is_compat) {
04347                 ok = RNA_property_collection_raw_set(NULL, &self->ptr, self->prop, attr, buf.buf, raw_type, tot);
04348             }
04349 
04350             PyBuffer_Release(&buf);
04351         }
04352 
04353         /* could not use the buffer, fallback to sequence */
04354         if (!buffer_is_compat) {
04355             array = PyMem_Malloc(size * tot);
04356 
04357             for ( ; i < tot; i++) {
04358                 item = PySequence_GetItem(seq, i);
04359                 switch (raw_type) {
04360                     case PROP_RAW_CHAR:
04361                         ((char *)array)[i] = (char)PyLong_AsLong(item);
04362                         break;
04363                     case PROP_RAW_SHORT:
04364                         ((short *)array)[i] = (short)PyLong_AsLong(item);
04365                         break;
04366                     case PROP_RAW_INT:
04367                         ((int *)array)[i] = (int)PyLong_AsLong(item);
04368                         break;
04369                     case PROP_RAW_FLOAT:
04370                         ((float *)array)[i] = (float)PyFloat_AsDouble(item);
04371                         break;
04372                     case PROP_RAW_DOUBLE:
04373                         ((double *)array)[i] = (double)PyFloat_AsDouble(item);
04374                         break;
04375                     case PROP_RAW_UNSET:
04376                         /* should never happen */
04377                         BLI_assert(!"Invalid array type - set");
04378                         break;
04379                 }
04380 
04381                 Py_DECREF(item);
04382             }
04383 
04384             ok = RNA_property_collection_raw_set(NULL, &self->ptr, self->prop, attr, array, raw_type, tot);
04385         }
04386     }
04387     else {
04388         buffer_is_compat = FALSE;
04389         if (PyObject_CheckBuffer(seq)) {
04390             Py_buffer buf;
04391             PyObject_GetBuffer(seq, &buf, PyBUF_SIMPLE | PyBUF_FORMAT);
04392 
04393             /* check if the buffer matches, TODO - signed/unsigned types */
04394 
04395             buffer_is_compat = foreach_compat_buffer(raw_type, attr_signed, buf.format);
04396 
04397             if (buffer_is_compat) {
04398                 ok = RNA_property_collection_raw_get(NULL, &self->ptr, self->prop, attr, buf.buf, raw_type, tot);
04399             }
04400 
04401             PyBuffer_Release(&buf);
04402         }
04403 
04404         /* could not use the buffer, fallback to sequence */
04405         if (!buffer_is_compat) {
04406             array = PyMem_Malloc(size * tot);
04407 
04408             ok = RNA_property_collection_raw_get(NULL, &self->ptr, self->prop, attr, array, raw_type, tot);
04409 
04410             if (!ok) i = tot;  /* skip the loop */
04411 
04412             for ( ; i < tot; i++) {
04413 
04414                 switch (raw_type) {
04415                     case PROP_RAW_CHAR:
04416                         item = PyLong_FromSsize_t((Py_ssize_t) ((char *)array)[i]);
04417                         break;
04418                     case PROP_RAW_SHORT:
04419                         item = PyLong_FromSsize_t((Py_ssize_t) ((short *)array)[i]);
04420                         break;
04421                     case PROP_RAW_INT:
04422                         item = PyLong_FromSsize_t((Py_ssize_t) ((int *)array)[i]);
04423                         break;
04424                     case PROP_RAW_FLOAT:
04425                         item = PyFloat_FromDouble((double) ((float *)array)[i]);
04426                         break;
04427                     case PROP_RAW_DOUBLE:
04428                         item = PyFloat_FromDouble((double) ((double *)array)[i]);
04429                         break;
04430                     default: /* PROP_RAW_UNSET */
04431                         /* should never happen */
04432                         BLI_assert(!"Invalid array type - get");
04433                         item = Py_None;
04434                         Py_INCREF(item);
04435                         break;
04436                 }
04437 
04438                 PySequence_SetItem(seq, i, item);
04439                 Py_DECREF(item);
04440             }
04441         }
04442     }
04443 
04444     if (array)
04445         PyMem_Free(array);
04446 
04447     if (PyErr_Occurred()) {
04448         /* Maybe we could make our own error */
04449         PyErr_Print();
04450         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "couldn't access the py sequence");
04451         return NULL;
04452     }
04453     if (!ok) {
04454         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError, "internal error setting the array");
04455         return NULL;
04456     }
04457 
04458     Py_RETURN_NONE;
04459 }

04607 /* only needed for subtyping, so a new class gets a valid BPy_StructRNA
04608  * todo - also accept useful args */
04609 static PyObject *pyrna_struct_new(PyTypeObject *type, PyObject *args, PyObject *UNUSED(kwds))
04610 {
04611     if (PyTuple_GET_SIZE(args) == 1) {
04612         BPy_StructRNA *base = (BPy_StructRNA *)PyTuple_GET_ITEM(args, 0);
04613         if (Py_TYPE(base) == type) {
04614             Py_INCREF(base);
04615             return (PyObject *)base;
04616         }
04617         else if (PyType_IsSubtype(Py_TYPE(base), &pyrna_struct_Type)) {
04618             /* this almost never runs, only when using user defined subclasses of built-in object.
04619              * this isn't common since its NOT related to registerable subclasses. eg:
04620              *
04621              *  >>> class MyObSubclass(bpy.types.Object):
04622              *  ...     def test_func(self):
04623              *  ...         print(100)
04624              *  ...
04625              *  >>> myob = MyObSubclass(bpy.context.object)
04626              *  >>> myob.test_func()
04627              *  100
04628              *
04629              * Keep this since it could be useful.
04630              */
04631             BPy_StructRNA *ret;
04632             if ((ret = (BPy_StructRNA *)type->tp_alloc(type, 0))) {
04633                 ret->ptr = base->ptr;
04634             }
04635             /* pass on exception & NULL if tp_alloc fails */
04636             return (PyObject *)ret;
04637         }
04638 
04639         /* error, invalid type given */
04640         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
04641                      "bpy_struct.__new__(type): type '%.200s' is not a subtype of bpy_struct",
04642                      type->tp_name);
04643         return NULL;
04644     }
04645     else {
04646         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
04647                      "bpy_struct.__new__(type): expected a single argument");
04648         return NULL;
04649     }
04650 }

04679 static PyObject *pyrna_param_to_py(PointerRNA *ptr, PropertyRNA *prop, void *data)
04680 {
04681     PyObject *ret;
04682     const int type = RNA_property_type(prop);
04683     const int flag = RNA_property_flag(prop);
04684 
04685     if (RNA_property_array_check(prop)) {
04686         int a, len;
04687 
04688         if (flag & PROP_DYNAMIC) {
04689             ParameterDynAlloc *data_alloc = data;
04690             len = data_alloc->array_tot;
04691             data = data_alloc->array;
04692         }
04693         else
04694             len = RNA_property_array_length(ptr, prop);
04695 
04696         /* resolve the array from a new pytype */
04697 
04698         /* kazanbas: TODO make multidim sequences here */
04699 
04700         switch (type) {
04701             case PROP_BOOLEAN:
04702                 ret = PyTuple_New(len);
04703                 for (a = 0; a < len; a++)
04704                     PyTuple_SET_ITEM(ret, a, PyBool_FromLong(((int *)data)[a]));
04705                 break;
04706             case PROP_INT:
04707                 ret = PyTuple_New(len);
04708                 for (a = 0; a < len; a++)
04709                     PyTuple_SET_ITEM(ret, a, PyLong_FromSsize_t((Py_ssize_t)((int *)data)[a]));
04710                 break;
04711             case PROP_FLOAT:
04712                 switch (RNA_property_subtype(prop)) {
04713 #ifdef USE_MATHUTILS
04714                     case PROP_ALL_VECTOR_SUBTYPES:
04715                         ret = Vector_CreatePyObject(data, len, Py_NEW, NULL);
04716                         break;
04717                     case PROP_MATRIX:
04718                         if (len == 16) {
04719                             ret = Matrix_CreatePyObject(data, 4, 4, Py_NEW, NULL);
04720                             break;
04721                         }
04722                         else if (len == 9) {
04723                             ret = Matrix_CreatePyObject(data, 3, 3, Py_NEW, NULL);
04724                             break;
04725                         }
04726                         /* pass through */
04727 #endif
04728                     default:
04729                         ret = PyTuple_New(len);
04730                         for (a = 0; a < len; a++)
04731                             PyTuple_SET_ITEM(ret, a, PyFloat_FromDouble(((float *)data)[a]));
04732 
04733                 }
04734                 break;
04735             default:
04736                 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
04737                              "RNA Error: unknown array type \"%d\" (pyrna_param_to_py)",
04738                              type);
04739                 ret = NULL;
04740                 break;
04741         }
04742     }
04743     else {
04744         /* see if we can coorce into a python type - PropertyType */
04745         switch (type) {
04746             case PROP_BOOLEAN:
04747                 ret = PyBool_FromLong(*(int *)data);
04748                 break;
04749             case PROP_INT:
04750                 ret = PyLong_FromSsize_t((Py_ssize_t)*(int *)data);
04751                 break;
04752             case PROP_FLOAT:
04753                 ret = PyFloat_FromDouble(*(float *)data);
04754                 break;
04755             case PROP_STRING:
04756             {
04757                 char *data_ch;
04758                 PyObject *value_coerce = NULL;
04759                 const int subtype = RNA_property_subtype(prop);
04760 
04761                 if (flag & PROP_THICK_WRAP)
04762                     data_ch = (char *)data;
04763                 else
04764                     data_ch = *(char **)data;
04765 
04766 #ifdef USE_STRING_COERCE
04767                 if (subtype == PROP_BYTESTRING) {
04768                     ret = PyBytes_FromString(data_ch);
04769                 }
04770                 else if (ELEM3(subtype, PROP_FILEPATH, PROP_DIRPATH, PROP_FILENAME)) {
04771                     ret = PyC_UnicodeFromByte(data_ch);
04772                 }
04773                 else {
04774                     ret = PyUnicode_FromString(data_ch);
04775                 }
04776 #else
04777                 if (subtype == PROP_BYTESTRING) {
04778                     ret = PyBytes_FromString(buf);
04779                 }
04780                 else {
04781                     ret = PyUnicode_FromString(data_ch);
04782                 }
04783 #endif
04784 
04785 #ifdef USE_STRING_COERCE
04786                 Py_XDECREF(value_coerce);
04787 #endif
04788 
04789                 break;
04790             }
04791             case PROP_ENUM:
04792             {
04793                 ret = pyrna_enum_to_py(ptr, prop, *(int *)data);
04794                 break;
04795             }
04796             case PROP_POINTER:
04797             {
04798                 PointerRNA newptr;
04799                 StructRNA *ptype = RNA_property_pointer_type(ptr, prop);
04800 
04801                 if (flag & PROP_RNAPTR) {
04802                     /* in this case we get the full ptr */
04803                     newptr = *(PointerRNA *)data;
04804                 }
04805                 else {
04806                     if (RNA_struct_is_ID(ptype)) {
04807                         RNA_id_pointer_create(*(void **)data, &newptr);
04808                     }
04809                     else {
04810                         /* note: this is taken from the function's ID pointer
04811                          * and will break if a function returns a pointer from
04812                          * another ID block, watch this! - it should at least be
04813                          * easy to debug since they are all ID's */
04814                         RNA_pointer_create(ptr->id.data, ptype, *(void **)data, &newptr);
04815                     }
04816                 }
04817 
04818                 if (newptr.data) {
04819                     ret = pyrna_struct_CreatePyObject(&newptr);
04820                 }
04821                 else {
04822                     ret = Py_None;
04823                     Py_INCREF(ret);
04824                 }
04825                 break;
04826             }
04827             case PROP_COLLECTION:
04828             {
04829                 ListBase *lb = (ListBase *)data;
04830                 CollectionPointerLink *link;
04831                 PyObject *linkptr;
04832 
04833                 ret = PyList_New(0);
04834 
04835                 for (link = lb->first; link; link = link->next) {
04836                     linkptr = pyrna_struct_CreatePyObject(&link->ptr);
04837                     PyList_Append(ret, linkptr);
04838                     Py_DECREF(linkptr);
04839                 }
04840 
04841                 break;
04842             }
04843             default:
04844                 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
04845                              "RNA Error: unknown type \"%d\" (pyrna_param_to_py)",
04846                              type);
04847                 ret = NULL;
04848                 break;
04849         }
04850     }
04851 
04852     return ret;
04853 }

04855 /* Use to replace PyDict_GetItemString() when the overhead of converting a
04856  * string into a python unicode is higher than a non hash lookup.
04857  * works on small dict's such as keyword args. */
04858 static PyObject *small_dict_get_item_string(PyObject *dict, const char *key_lookup)
04859 {
04860     PyObject *key = NULL;
04861     Py_ssize_t pos = 0;
04862     PyObject *value = NULL;
04863 
04864     while (PyDict_Next(dict, &pos, &key, &value)) {
04865         if (PyUnicode_Check(key)) {
04866             if (strcmp(key_lookup, _PyUnicode_AsString(key)) == 0) {
04867                 return value;
04868             }
04869         }
04870     }
04871 
04872     return NULL;
04873 }
