04875 static PyObject *pyrna_func_call(BPy_FunctionRNA *self, PyObject *args, PyObject *kw)
04876 {
04877     /* Note, both BPy_StructRNA and BPy_PropertyRNA can be used here */
04878     PointerRNA *self_ptr = &self->ptr;
04879     FunctionRNA *self_func = self->func;
04880 
04881     PointerRNA funcptr;
04882     ParameterList parms;
04883     ParameterIterator iter;
04884     PropertyRNA *parm;
04885     PyObject *ret, *item;
04886     int i, pyargs_len, pykw_len, parms_len, ret_len, flag, err = 0, kw_tot = 0, kw_arg;
04887 
04888     PropertyRNA *pret_single = NULL;
04889     void *retdata_single = NULL;
04890 
04891     /* enable this so all strings are copied and freed after calling.
04892      * this exposes bugs where the pointer to the string is held and re-used */
04893 // #define DEBUG_STRING_FREE
04894 
04895 #ifdef DEBUG_STRING_FREE
04896     PyObject *string_free_ls = PyList_New(0);
04897 #endif
04898 
04899     /* Should never happen but it does in rare cases */
04900     BLI_assert(self_ptr != NULL);
04901 
04902     if (self_ptr == NULL) {
04903         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError, "rna functions internal rna pointer is NULL, this is a bug. aborting");
04904         return NULL;
04905     }
04906 
04907     if (self_func == NULL) {
04908         PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
04909                      "%.200s.<unknown>(): rna function internal function is NULL, this is a bug. aborting",
04910                      RNA_struct_identifier(self_ptr->type));
04911         return NULL;
04912     }
04913 
04914     /* for testing */
04915 #if 0
04916     {
04917         const char *fn;
04918         int lineno;
04919         PyC_FileAndNum(&fn, &lineno);
04920         printf("pyrna_func_call > %.200s.%.200s : %.200s:%d\n",
04921                RNA_struct_identifier(self_ptr->type), RNA_function_identifier(self_func), fn, lineno);
04922     }
04923 #endif
04924 
04925     /* include the ID pointer for pyrna_param_to_py() so we can include the
04926      * ID pointer on return values, this only works when returned values have
04927      * the same ID as the functions. */
04928     RNA_pointer_create(self_ptr->id.data, &RNA_Function, self_func, &funcptr);
04929 
04930     pyargs_len = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(args);
04931     pykw_len = kw ? PyDict_Size(kw) : 0;
04932 
04933     RNA_parameter_list_create(&parms, self_ptr, self_func);
04934     RNA_parameter_list_begin(&parms, &iter);
04935     parms_len = RNA_parameter_list_arg_count(&parms);
04936     ret_len = 0;
04937 
04938     if (pyargs_len + pykw_len > parms_len) {
04939         RNA_parameter_list_end(&iter);
04940         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
04941                      "%.200s.%.200s(): takes at most %d arguments, got %d",
04942                      RNA_struct_identifier(self_ptr->type), RNA_function_identifier(self_func),
04943                      parms_len, pyargs_len + pykw_len);
04944         err = -1;
04945     }
04946 
04947     /* parse function parameters */
04948     for (i = 0; iter.valid && err == 0; RNA_parameter_list_next(&iter)) {
04949         parm = iter.parm;
04950         flag = RNA_property_flag(parm);
04951 
04952         /* only useful for single argument returns, we'll need another list loop for multiple */
04953         if (flag & PROP_OUTPUT) {
04954             ret_len++;
04955             if (pret_single == NULL) {
04956                 pret_single = parm;
04957                 retdata_single = iter.data;
04958             }
04959 
04960             continue;
04961         }
04962 
04963         item = NULL;
04964 
04965         if (i < pyargs_len) {
04966             item = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(args, i);
04967             kw_arg = FALSE;
04968         }
04969         else if (kw != NULL) {
04970 #if 0
04971             item = PyDict_GetItemString(kw, RNA_property_identifier(parm)); /* borrow ref */
04972 #else
04973             item = small_dict_get_item_string(kw, RNA_property_identifier(parm)); /* borrow ref */
04974 #endif
04975             if (item)
04976                 kw_tot++;  /* make sure invalid keywords are not given */
04977 
04978             kw_arg = TRUE;
04979         }
04980 
04981         i++; /* current argument */
04982 
04983         if (item == NULL) {
04984             if (flag & PROP_REQUIRED) {
04985                 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
04986                              "%.200s.%.200s(): required parameter \"%.200s\" not specified",
04987                              RNA_struct_identifier(self_ptr->type),
04988                              RNA_function_identifier(self_func),
04989                              RNA_property_identifier(parm));
04990                 err = -1;
04991                 break;
04992             }
04993             else { /* PyDict_GetItemString wont raise an error */
04994                 continue;
04995             }
04996         }
04997 
04998 #ifdef DEBUG_STRING_FREE
04999         if (item) {
05000             if (PyUnicode_Check(item)) {
05001                 item = PyUnicode_FromString(_PyUnicode_AsString(item));
05002                 PyList_Append(string_free_ls, item);
05003                 Py_DECREF(item);
05004             }
05005         }
05006 #endif
05007         err = pyrna_py_to_prop(&funcptr, parm, iter.data, item, "");
05008 
05009         if (err != 0) {
05010             /* the error generated isn't that useful, so generate it again with a useful prefix
05011              * could also write a function to prepend to error messages */
05012             char error_prefix[512];
05013             PyErr_Clear(); /* re-raise */
05014 
05015             if (kw_arg == TRUE)
05016                 BLI_snprintf(error_prefix, sizeof(error_prefix),
05017                              "%.200s.%.200s(): error with keyword argument \"%.200s\" - ",
05018                              RNA_struct_identifier(self_ptr->type),
05019                              RNA_function_identifier(self_func),
05020                              RNA_property_identifier(parm));
05021             else
05022                 BLI_snprintf(error_prefix, sizeof(error_prefix),
05023                              "%.200s.%.200s(): error with argument %d, \"%.200s\" - ",
05024                              RNA_struct_identifier(self_ptr->type),
05025                              RNA_function_identifier(self_func),
05026                              i,
05027                              RNA_property_identifier(parm));
05028 
05029             pyrna_py_to_prop(&funcptr, parm, iter.data, item, error_prefix);
05030 
05031             break;
05032         }
05033     }
05034 
05035     RNA_parameter_list_end(&iter);
05036 
05037     /* Check if we gave args that don't exist in the function
05038      * printing the error is slow but it should only happen when developing.
05039      * the if below is quick, checking if it passed less keyword args then we gave.
05040      * (Don't overwrite the error if we have one, otherwise can skip important messages and confuse with args)
05041      */
05042     if (err == 0 && kw && (pykw_len > kw_tot)) {
05043         PyObject *key, *value;
05044         Py_ssize_t pos = 0;
05045 
05046         DynStr *bad_args = BLI_dynstr_new();
05047         DynStr *good_args = BLI_dynstr_new();
05048 
05049         const char *arg_name, *bad_args_str, *good_args_str;
05050         int found = FALSE, first = TRUE;
05051 
05052         while (PyDict_Next(kw, &pos, &key, &value)) {
05053 
05054             arg_name = _PyUnicode_AsString(key);
05055             found = FALSE;
05056 
05057             if (arg_name == NULL) { /* unlikely the argname is not a string but ignore if it is*/
05058                 PyErr_Clear();
05059             }
05060             else {
05061                 /* Search for arg_name */
05062                 RNA_parameter_list_begin(&parms, &iter);
05063                 for (; iter.valid; RNA_parameter_list_next(&iter)) {
05064                     parm = iter.parm;
05065                     if (strcmp(arg_name, RNA_property_identifier(parm)) == 0) {
05066                         found = TRUE;
05067                         break;
05068                     }
05069                 }
05070 
05071                 RNA_parameter_list_end(&iter);
05072 
05073                 if (found == FALSE) {
05074                     BLI_dynstr_appendf(bad_args, first ? "%s" : ", %s", arg_name);
05075                     first = FALSE;
05076                 }
05077             }
05078         }
05079 
05080         /* list good args */
05081         first = TRUE;
05082 
05083         RNA_parameter_list_begin(&parms, &iter);
05084         for (; iter.valid; RNA_parameter_list_next(&iter)) {
05085             parm = iter.parm;
05086             if (RNA_property_flag(parm) & PROP_OUTPUT)
05087                 continue;
05088 
05089             BLI_dynstr_appendf(good_args, first ? "%s" : ", %s", RNA_property_identifier(parm));
05090             first = FALSE;
05091         }
05092         RNA_parameter_list_end(&iter);
05093 
05094 
05095         bad_args_str = BLI_dynstr_get_cstring(bad_args);
05096         good_args_str = BLI_dynstr_get_cstring(good_args);
05097 
05098         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
05099                      "%.200s.%.200s(): was called with invalid keyword arguments(s) (%s), expected (%s)",
05100                      RNA_struct_identifier(self_ptr->type), RNA_function_identifier(self_func),
05101                      bad_args_str, good_args_str);
05102 
05103         BLI_dynstr_free(bad_args);
05104         BLI_dynstr_free(good_args);
05105         MEM_freeN((void *)bad_args_str);
05106         MEM_freeN((void *)good_args_str);
05107 
05108         err = -1;
05109     }
05110 
05111     ret = NULL;
05112     if (err == 0) {
05113         /* call function */
05114         ReportList reports;
05115         bContext *C = BPy_GetContext();
05116 
05117         BKE_reports_init(&reports, RPT_STORE);
05118         RNA_function_call(C, &reports, self_ptr, self_func, &parms);
05119 
05120         err = (BPy_reports_to_error(&reports, PyExc_RuntimeError, TRUE));
05121 
05122         /* return value */
05123         if (err != -1) {
05124             if (ret_len > 0) {
05125                 if (ret_len > 1) {
05126                     ret = PyTuple_New(ret_len);
05127                     i = 0; /* arg index */
05128 
05129                     RNA_parameter_list_begin(&parms, &iter);
05130 
05131                     for (; iter.valid; RNA_parameter_list_next(&iter)) {
05132                         parm = iter.parm;
05133                         flag = RNA_property_flag(parm);
05134 
05135                         if (flag & PROP_OUTPUT)
05136                             PyTuple_SET_ITEM(ret, i++, pyrna_param_to_py(&funcptr, parm, iter.data));
05137                     }
05138 
05139                     RNA_parameter_list_end(&iter);
05140                 }
05141                 else
05142                     ret = pyrna_param_to_py(&funcptr, pret_single, retdata_single);
05143 
05144                 /* possible there is an error in conversion */
05145                 if (ret == NULL)
05146                     err = -1;
05147             }
05148         }
05149     }
05150 
05151 
05152 #ifdef DEBUG_STRING_FREE
05153 #if 0
05154     if (PyList_GET_SIZE(string_free_ls)) {
05155         printf("%.200s.%.200s():  has %d strings\n",
05156                RNA_struct_identifier(self_ptr->type),
05157                RNA_function_identifier(self_func),
05158                (int)PyList_GET_SIZE(string_free_ls));
05159     }
05160 #endif
05161     Py_DECREF(string_free_ls);
05162 #undef DEBUG_STRING_FREE
05163 #endif
05164 
05165     /* cleanup */
05166     RNA_parameter_list_end(&iter);
05167     RNA_parameter_list_free(&parms);
05168 
05169     if (ret)
05170         return ret;
05171 
05172     if (err == -1)
05173         return NULL;
05174 
05175     Py_RETURN_NONE;
05176 }

05916         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_StopIteration, "pyrna_prop_collection_iter stop");

05960     PyObject *item;

06011 /* check if we have a native python subclass, use it when it exists
06012  * return a borrowed reference */
06013 static PyObject *bpy_types_dict = NULL;
06014 
06015 static PyObject *pyrna_srna_ExternalType(StructRNA *srna)
06016 {
06017     const char *idname = RNA_struct_identifier(srna);
06018     PyObject *newclass;
06019 
06020     if (bpy_types_dict == NULL) {
06021         PyObject *bpy_types = PyImport_ImportModuleLevel((char *)"bpy_types", NULL, NULL, NULL, 0);
06022 
06023         if (bpy_types == NULL) {
06024             PyErr_Print();
06025             PyErr_Clear();
06026             fprintf(stderr, "%s: failed to find 'bpy_types' module\n", __func__);
06027             return NULL;
06028         }
06029         bpy_types_dict = PyModule_GetDict(bpy_types); // borrow
06030         Py_DECREF(bpy_types); // fairly safe to assume the dict is kept
06031     }
06032 
06033     newclass = PyDict_GetItemString(bpy_types_dict, idname);
06034 
06035     /* sanity check, could skip this unless in debug mode */
06036     if (newclass) {
06037         PyObject *base_compare = pyrna_srna_PyBase(srna);
06038         //PyObject *slots = PyObject_GetAttrString(newclass, "__slots__"); // cant do this because it gets superclasses values!
06039         //PyObject *bases = PyObject_GetAttrString(newclass, "__bases__"); // can do this but faster not to.
06040         PyObject *tp_bases = ((PyTypeObject *)newclass)->tp_bases;
06041         PyObject *tp_slots = PyDict_GetItem(((PyTypeObject *)newclass)->tp_dict, bpy_intern_str___slots__);
06042 
06043         if (tp_slots == NULL) {
06044             fprintf(stderr, "%s: expected class '%s' to have __slots__ defined\n\nSee bpy_types.py\n", __func__, idname);
06045             newclass = NULL;
06046         }
06047         else if (PyTuple_GET_SIZE(tp_bases)) {
06048             PyObject *base = PyTuple_GET_ITEM(tp_bases, 0);
06049 
06050             if (base_compare != base) {
06051                 fprintf(stderr, "%s: incorrect subclassing of SRNA '%s'\nSee bpy_types.py\n", __func__, idname);
06052                 PyC_ObSpit("Expected! ", base_compare);
06053                 newclass = NULL;
06054             }
06055             else {
06056                 if (G.debug & G_DEBUG_PYTHON)
06057                     fprintf(stderr, "SRNA Subclassed: '%s'\n", idname);
06058             }
06059         }
06060     }
06061 
06062     return newclass;
06063 }

06065 static PyObject *pyrna_srna_Subtype(StructRNA *srna)
06066 {
06067     PyObject *newclass = NULL;
06068 
06069     /* stupid/simple case */
06070     if (srna == NULL) {
06071         newclass = NULL; /* Nothing to do */
06072     }   /* the class may have already been declared & allocated */
06073     else if ((newclass = RNA_struct_py_type_get(srna))) {
06074         Py_INCREF(newclass);
06075     }   /* check if bpy_types.py module has the class defined in it */
06076     else if ((newclass = pyrna_srna_ExternalType(srna))) {
06077         pyrna_subtype_set_rna(newclass, srna);
06078         Py_INCREF(newclass);
06079     }   /* create a new class instance with the C api
06080          * mainly for the purposing of matching the C/rna type hierarchy */
06081     else {
06082         /* subclass equivalents
06083          * - class myClass(myBase):
06084          *     some = 'value' # or ...
06085          * - myClass = type(name='myClass', bases=(myBase,), dict={'__module__':'bpy.types'})
06086          */
06087 
06088         /* Assume RNA_struct_py_type_get(srna) was already checked */
06089         PyObject *py_base = pyrna_srna_PyBase(srna);
06090         PyObject *metaclass;
06091         const char *idname = RNA_struct_identifier(srna);
06092 
06093         /* remove __doc__ for now */
06094         // const char *descr = RNA_struct_ui_description(srna);
06095         // if (!descr) descr = "(no docs)";
06096         // "__doc__", descr
06097 
06098         if (RNA_struct_idprops_check(srna) &&
06099             !PyObject_IsSubclass(py_base, (PyObject *)&pyrna_struct_meta_idprop_Type))
06100         {
06101             metaclass = (PyObject *)&pyrna_struct_meta_idprop_Type;
06102         }
06103         else {
06104             metaclass = (PyObject *)&PyType_Type;
06105         }
06106 
06107         /* always use O not N when calling, N causes refcount errors */
06108         newclass = PyObject_CallFunction(metaclass, (char *)"s(O) {sss()}",
06109                                          idname, py_base, "__module__", "bpy.types", "__slots__");
06110 
06111         /* newclass will now have 2 ref's, ???, probably 1 is internal since decrefing here segfaults */
06112 
06113         /* PyC_ObSpit("new class ref", newclass); */
06114 
06115         if (newclass) {
06116             /* srna owns one, and the other is owned by the caller */
06117             pyrna_subtype_set_rna(newclass, srna);
06118 
06119             // XXX, adding this back segfaults blender on load.
06120             // Py_DECREF(newclass); /* let srna own */
06121         }
06122         else {
06123             /* this should not happen */
06124             printf("%s: error registering '%s'\n", __func__, idname);
06125             PyErr_Print();
06126             PyErr_Clear();
06127         }
06128     }
06129 
06130     return newclass;
06131 }

06150 /*-----------------------CreatePyObject---------------------------------*/
06151 PyObject *pyrna_struct_CreatePyObject(PointerRNA *ptr)
06152 {
06153     BPy_StructRNA *pyrna = NULL;
06154 
06155     /* note: don't rely on this to return None since NULL data with a valid type can often crash */
06156     if (ptr->data == NULL && ptr->type == NULL) { /* Operator RNA has NULL data */
06157         Py_RETURN_NONE;
06158     }
06159     else {
06160         PyTypeObject *tp = (PyTypeObject *)pyrna_struct_Subtype(ptr);
06161 
06162         if (tp) {
06163             pyrna = (BPy_StructRNA *) tp->tp_alloc(tp, 0);
06164             Py_DECREF(tp); /* srna owns, cant hold a ref */
06165         }
06166         else {
06167             fprintf(stderr, "%s: could not make type\n", __func__);
06168             pyrna = (BPy_StructRNA *) PyObject_GC_New(BPy_StructRNA, &pyrna_struct_Type);
06169 #ifdef USE_WEAKREFS
06170             pyrna->in_weakreflist = NULL;
06171 #endif
06172         }
06173     }
06174 
06175     if (pyrna == NULL) {
06176         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_MemoryError, "couldn't create bpy_struct object");
06177         return NULL;
06178     }
06179 
06180     pyrna->ptr = *ptr;
06181 #ifdef PYRNA_FREE_SUPPORT
06182     pyrna->freeptr = FALSE;
06183 #endif
06184 
06185 #ifdef USE_PYRNA_STRUCT_REFERENCE
06186     pyrna->reference = NULL;
06187 #endif
06188 
06189     // PyC_ObSpit("NewStructRNA: ", (PyObject *)pyrna);
06190 
06191 #ifdef USE_PYRNA_INVALIDATE_WEAKREF
06192     if (ptr->id.data) {
06193         id_weakref_pool_add(ptr->id.data, (BPy_DummyPointerRNA *)pyrna);
06194     }
06195 #endif
06196     return (PyObject *)pyrna;
06197 }

06453 StructRNA *pyrna_struct_as_srna(PyObject *self, int parent, const char *error_prefix)
06454 {
06455     BPy_StructRNA *py_srna = NULL;
06456     StructRNA *srna;
06457 
06458     /* ack, PyObject_GetAttrString wont look up this types tp_dict first :/ */
06459     if (PyType_Check(self)) {
06460         py_srna = (BPy_StructRNA *)PyDict_GetItem(((PyTypeObject *)self)->tp_dict, bpy_intern_str_bl_rna);
06461         Py_XINCREF(py_srna);
06462     }
06463 
06464     if (parent) {
06465         /* be very careful with this since it will return a parent classes srna.
06466          * modifying this will do confusing stuff! */
06467         if (py_srna == NULL)
06468             py_srna = (BPy_StructRNA *)PyObject_GetAttr(self, bpy_intern_str_bl_rna);
06469     }
06470 
06471     if (py_srna == NULL) {
06472         PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
06473                      "%.200s, missing bl_rna attribute from '%.200s' instance (may not be registered)",
06474                      error_prefix, Py_TYPE(self)->tp_name);
06475         return NULL;
06476     }
06477 
06478     if (!BPy_StructRNA_Check(py_srna)) {
06479         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
06480                      "%.200s, bl_rna attribute wrong type '%.200s' on '%.200s'' instance",
06481                      error_prefix, Py_TYPE(py_srna)->tp_name,
06482                      Py_TYPE(self)->tp_name);
06483         Py_DECREF(py_srna);
06484         return NULL;
06485     }
06486 
06487     if (py_srna->ptr.type != &RNA_Struct) {
06488         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
06489                      "%.200s, bl_rna attribute not a RNA_Struct, on '%.200s'' instance",
06490                      error_prefix, Py_TYPE(self)->tp_name);
06491         Py_DECREF(py_srna);
06492         return NULL;
06493     }
06494 
06495     srna = py_srna->ptr.data;
06496     Py_DECREF(py_srna);
06497 
06498     return srna;
06499 }

06501 /* Orphan functions, not sure where they should go */
06502 /* get the srna for methods attached to types */
06503 /*
06504  * Caller needs to raise error.*/
06505 StructRNA *srna_from_self(PyObject *self, const char *error_prefix)
06506 {
06507 
06508     if (self == NULL) {
06509         return NULL;
06510     }
06511     else if (PyCapsule_CheckExact(self)) {
06512         return PyCapsule_GetPointer(self, NULL);
06513     }
06514     else if (PyType_Check(self) == 0) {
06515         return NULL;
06516     }
06517     else {
06518         /* These cases above not errors, they just mean the type was not compatible
06519          * After this any errors will be raised in the script */
06520 
06521         PyObject *error_type, *error_value, *error_traceback;
06522         StructRNA *srna;
06523 
06524         PyErr_Fetch(&error_type, &error_value, &error_traceback);
06525         PyErr_Clear();
06526 
06527         srna = pyrna_struct_as_srna(self, 0, error_prefix);
06528 
06529         if (!PyErr_Occurred()) {
06530             PyErr_Restore(error_type, error_value, error_traceback);
06531         }
06532 
06533         return srna;
06534     }
06535 }

06537 static int deferred_register_prop(StructRNA *srna, PyObject *key, PyObject *item)
06538 {
06539     /* We only care about results from C which
06540      * are for sure types, save some time with error */
06541     if (pyrna_is_deferred_prop(item)) {
06542 
06543         PyObject *py_func, *py_kw, *py_srna_cobject, *py_ret;
06544 
06545         if (PyArg_ParseTuple(item, "OO!", &py_func, &PyDict_Type, &py_kw)) {
06546             PyObject *args_fake;
06547 
06548             if (*_PyUnicode_AsString(key) == '_') {
06549                 PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
06550                              "bpy_struct \"%.200s\" registration error: "
06551                              "%.200s could not register because the property starts with an '_'\n",
06552                              RNA_struct_identifier(srna), _PyUnicode_AsString(key));
06553                 return -1;
06554             }
06555             py_srna_cobject = PyCapsule_New(srna, NULL, NULL);
06556 
06557             /* not 100% nice :/, modifies the dict passed, should be ok */
06558             PyDict_SetItem(py_kw, bpy_intern_str_attr, key);
06559 
06560             args_fake = PyTuple_New(1);
06561             PyTuple_SET_ITEM(args_fake, 0, py_srna_cobject);
06562 
06563             py_ret = PyObject_Call(py_func, args_fake, py_kw);
06564 
06565             if (py_ret) {
06566                 Py_DECREF(py_ret);
06567                 Py_DECREF(args_fake); /* free's py_srna_cobject too */
06568             }
06569             else {
06570                 /* _must_ print before decreffing args_fake */
06571                 PyErr_Print();
06572                 PyErr_Clear();
06573 
06574                 Py_DECREF(args_fake); /* free's py_srna_cobject too */
06575 
06576                 // PyC_LineSpit();
06577                 PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
06578                              "bpy_struct \"%.200s\" registration error: "
06579                              "%.200s could not register\n",
06580                              RNA_struct_identifier(srna), _PyUnicode_AsString(key));
06581                 return -1;
06582             }
06583         }
06584         else {
06585             /* Since this is a class dict, ignore args that can't be passed */
06586 
06587             /* for testing only */
06588 #if 0
06589             PyC_ObSpit("Why doesn't this work??", item);
06590             PyErr_Print();
06591 #endif
06592             PyErr_Clear();
06593         }
06594     }
06595 
06596     return 0;
06597 }
06598 
06599 static int pyrna_deferred_register_props(StructRNA *srna, PyObject *class_dict)
06600 {
06601     PyObject *item, *key;
06602     PyObject *order;
06603     Py_ssize_t pos = 0;
06604     int ret = 0;
06605 
06606     /* in both cases PyDict_CheckExact(class_dict) will be true even
06607      * though Operators have a metaclass dict namespace */
06608 
06609     if ((order = PyDict_GetItem(class_dict, bpy_intern_str_order)) && PyList_CheckExact(order)) {
06610         for (pos = 0; pos < PyList_GET_SIZE(order); pos++) {
06611             key = PyList_GET_ITEM(order, pos);
06612             /* however unlikely its possible
06613              * fails in py 3.3 beta with __qualname__ */
06614             if ((item = PyDict_GetItem(class_dict, key))) {
06615                 ret = deferred_register_prop(srna, key, item);
06616                 if (ret != 0) {
06617                     break;
06618                 }
06619             }
06620         }
06621     }
06622     else {
06623         while (PyDict_Next(class_dict, &pos, &key, &item)) {
06624             ret = deferred_register_prop(srna, key, item);
06625 
06626             if (ret != 0)
06627                 break;
06628         }
06629     }
06630 
06631     return ret;
06632 }
06633 
06634 static int pyrna_deferred_register_class_recursive(StructRNA *srna, PyTypeObject *py_class)
06635 {
06636     const int len = PyTuple_GET_SIZE(py_class->tp_bases);
06637     int i, ret;
06638 
06639     /* first scan base classes for registerable properties */
06640     for (i = 0; i < len; i++) {
06641         PyTypeObject *py_superclass = (PyTypeObject *)PyTuple_GET_ITEM(py_class->tp_bases, i);
06642 
06643         /* the rules for using these base classes are not clear,
06644          * 'object' is of course not worth looking into and
06645          * existing subclasses of RNA would cause a lot more dictionary
06646          * looping then is needed (SomeOperator would scan Operator.__dict__)
06647          * which is harmless but not at all useful.
06648          *
06649          * So only scan base classes which are not subclasses if blender types.
06650          * This best fits having 'mix-in' classes for operators and render engines.
06651          */
06652         if (py_superclass != &PyBaseObject_Type &&
06653             !PyObject_IsSubclass((PyObject *)py_superclass, (PyObject *)&pyrna_struct_Type))
06654         {
06655             ret = pyrna_deferred_register_class_recursive(srna, py_superclass);
06656 
06657             if (ret != 0) {
06658                 return ret;
06659             }
06660         }
06661     }
06662 
06663     /* not register out own properties */
06664     return pyrna_deferred_register_props(srna, py_class->tp_dict); /* getattr(..., "__dict__") returns a proxy */
06665 }
06666 
06667 int pyrna_deferred_register_class(StructRNA *srna, PyObject *py_class)
06668 {
06669     /* Panels and Menus don't need this
06670      * save some time and skip the checks here */
06671     if (!RNA_struct_idprops_register_check(srna))
06672         return 0;
06673 
06674     return pyrna_deferred_register_class_recursive(srna, (PyTypeObject *)py_class);
06675 }

06679 static int rna_function_arg_count(FunctionRNA *func)
06680 {
06681     const ListBase *lb = RNA_function_defined_parameters(func);
06682     PropertyRNA *parm;
06683     Link *link;
06684     int count = (RNA_function_flag(func) & FUNC_NO_SELF) ? 0 : 1;
06685 
06686     for (link = lb->first; link; link = link->next) {
06687         parm = (PropertyRNA *)link;
06688         if (!(RNA_property_flag(parm) & PROP_OUTPUT))
06689             count++;
06690     }
06691 
06692     return count;
06693 }

06695 static int bpy_class_validate(PointerRNA *dummyptr, void *py_data, int *have_function)
06696 {
06697     const ListBase *lb;
06698     Link *link;
06699     FunctionRNA *func;
06700     PropertyRNA *prop;
06701     StructRNA *srna = dummyptr->type;
06702     const char *class_type = RNA_struct_identifier(srna);
06703     PyObject *py_class = (PyObject *)py_data;
06704     PyObject *base_class = RNA_struct_py_type_get(srna);
06705     PyObject *item;
06706     int i, flag, arg_count, func_arg_count;
06707     const char *py_class_name = ((PyTypeObject *)py_class)->tp_name; // __name__
06708 
06709 
06710     if (base_class) {
06711         if (!PyObject_IsSubclass(py_class, base_class)) {
06712             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
06713                          "expected %.200s subclass of class \"%.200s\"",
06714                          class_type, py_class_name);
06715             return -1;
06716         }
06717     }
06718 
06719     /* verify callback functions */
06720     lb = RNA_struct_type_functions(srna);
06721     i = 0;
06722     for (link = lb->first; link; link = link->next) {
06723         func = (FunctionRNA *)link;
06724         flag = RNA_function_flag(func);
06725 
06726         if (!(flag & FUNC_REGISTER))
06727             continue;
06728 
06729         item = PyObject_GetAttrString(py_class, RNA_function_identifier(func));
06730 
06731         have_function[i] = (item != NULL);
06732         i++;
06733 
06734         if (item == NULL) {
06735             if ((flag & FUNC_REGISTER_OPTIONAL) == 0) {
06736                 PyErr_Format(PyExc_AttributeError,
06737                              "expected %.200s, %.200s class to have an \"%.200s\" attribute",
06738                              class_type, py_class_name,
06739                              RNA_function_identifier(func));
06740                 return -1;
06741             }
06742 
06743             PyErr_Clear();
06744         }
06745         else {
06746             Py_DECREF(item); /* no need to keep a ref, the class owns it (technically we should keep a ref but...) */
06747             if (flag & FUNC_NO_SELF) {
06748                 if (PyMethod_Check(item) == 0) {
06749                     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
06750                                  "expected %.200s, %.200s class \"%.200s\" attribute to be a method, not a %.200s",
06751                                  class_type, py_class_name, RNA_function_identifier(func), Py_TYPE(item)->tp_name);
06752                     return -1;
06753                 }
06754                 item = ((PyMethodObject *)item)->im_func;
06755             }
06756             else {
06757                 if (PyFunction_Check(item) == 0) {
06758                     PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
06759                                  "expected %.200s, %.200s class \"%.200s\" attribute to be a function, not a %.200s",
06760                                  class_type, py_class_name, RNA_function_identifier(func), Py_TYPE(item)->tp_name);
06761                     return -1;
06762                 }
06763             }
06764 
06765             func_arg_count = rna_function_arg_count(func);
06766 
06767             if (func_arg_count >= 0) { /* -1 if we don't care*/
06768                 arg_count = ((PyCodeObject *)PyFunction_GET_CODE(item))->co_argcount;
06769 
06770                 /* note, the number of args we check for and the number of args we give to
06771                  * @classmethods are different (quirk of python),
06772                  * this is why rna_function_arg_count() doesn't return the value -1*/
06773                 if (flag & FUNC_NO_SELF)
06774                     func_arg_count++;
06775 
06776                 if (arg_count != func_arg_count) {
06777                     PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
06778                                  "expected %.200s, %.200s class \"%.200s\" function to have %d args, found %d",
06779                                  class_type, py_class_name, RNA_function_identifier(func),
06780                                  func_arg_count, arg_count);
06781                     return -1;
06782                 }
06783             }
06784         }
06785     }
06786 
06787     /* verify properties */
06788     lb = RNA_struct_type_properties(srna);
06789     for (link = lb->first; link; link = link->next) {
06790         const char *identifier;
06791         prop = (PropertyRNA *)link;
06792         flag = RNA_property_flag(prop);
06793 
06794         if (!(flag & PROP_REGISTER))
06795             continue;
06796 
06797         identifier = RNA_property_identifier(prop);
06798         item = PyObject_GetAttrString(py_class, identifier);
06799 
06800         if (item == NULL) {
06801             /* Sneaky workaround to use the class name as the bl_idname */
06802 
06803 #define     BPY_REPLACEMENT_STRING(rna_attr, py_attr)                         \
06804     if (strcmp(identifier, rna_attr) == 0) {                                  \
06805         item = PyObject_GetAttrString(py_class, py_attr);                     \
06806         if (item && item != Py_None) {                                        \
06807             if (pyrna_py_to_prop(dummyptr, prop, NULL,                        \
06808                                  item, "validating class:") != 0)             \
06809             {                                                                 \
06810                 Py_DECREF(item);                                              \
06811                 return -1;                                                    \
06812             }                                                                 \
06813         }                                                                     \
06814         Py_XDECREF(item);                                                     \
06815     }                                                                         \
06816 
06817 
06818             BPY_REPLACEMENT_STRING("bl_idname", "__name__");
06819             BPY_REPLACEMENT_STRING("bl_description", "__doc__");
06820 
06821 #undef      BPY_REPLACEMENT_STRING
06822 
06823             if (item == NULL && (((flag & PROP_REGISTER_OPTIONAL) != PROP_REGISTER_OPTIONAL))) {
06824                 PyErr_Format(PyExc_AttributeError,
06825                              "expected %.200s, %.200s class to have an \"%.200s\" attribute",
06826                              class_type, py_class_name, identifier);
06827                 return -1;
06828             }
06829 
06830             PyErr_Clear();
06831         }
06832         else {
06833             Py_DECREF(item); /* no need to keep a ref, the class owns it */
06834 
06835             if (pyrna_py_to_prop(dummyptr, prop, NULL, item, "validating class:") != 0)
06836                 return -1;
06837         }
06838     }
06839 
06840     return 0;
06841 }
06842 
06843 /* TODO - multiple return values like with rna functions */
06844 static int bpy_class_call(bContext *C, PointerRNA *ptr, FunctionRNA *func, ParameterList *parms)
06845 {
06846     PyObject *args;
06847     PyObject *ret = NULL, *py_srna = NULL, *py_class_instance = NULL, *parmitem;
06848     PyTypeObject *py_class;
06849     void **py_class_instance_store = NULL;
06850     PropertyRNA *parm;
06851     ParameterIterator iter;
06852     PointerRNA funcptr;
06853     int err = 0, i, flag, ret_len = 0;
06854     const char is_static = (RNA_function_flag(func) & FUNC_NO_SELF) != 0;
06855 
06856     /* annoying!, need to check if the screen gets set to NULL which is a
06857      * hint that the file was actually re-loaded. */
06858     char is_valid_wm;
06859 
06860     PropertyRNA *pret_single = NULL;
06861     void *retdata_single = NULL;
06862 
06863     PyGILState_STATE gilstate;
06864 
06865 #ifdef USE_PEDANTIC_WRITE
06866     const int is_operator = RNA_struct_is_a(ptr->type, &RNA_Operator);
06867     const char *func_id = RNA_function_identifier(func);
06868     /* testing, for correctness, not operator and not draw function */
06869     const short is_readonly = ((strncmp("draw", func_id, 4) == 0) || /* draw or draw_header */
06870                                /*strstr("render", func_id) ||*/
06871                                !is_operator);
06872 #endif
06873 
06874     py_class = RNA_struct_py_type_get(ptr->type);
06875     /* rare case. can happen when registering subclasses */
06876     if (py_class == NULL) {
06877         fprintf(stderr, "%s: unable to get python class for rna struct '%.200s'\n",
06878                 __func__, RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type));
06879         return -1;
06880     }
06881 
06882     /* XXX, this is needed because render engine calls without a context
06883      * this should be supported at some point but at the moment its not! */
06884     if (C == NULL)
06885         C = BPy_GetContext();
06886 
06887     is_valid_wm = (CTX_wm_manager(C) != NULL);
06888 
06889     bpy_context_set(C, &gilstate);
06890 
06891     if (!is_static) {
06892         /* some datatypes (operator, render engine) can store PyObjects for re-use */
06893         if (ptr->data) {
06894             void **instance = RNA_struct_instance(ptr);
06895 
06896             if (instance) {
06897                 if (*instance) {
06898                     py_class_instance = *instance;
06899                     Py_INCREF(py_class_instance);
06900                 }
06901                 else {
06902                     /* store the instance here once its created */
06903                     py_class_instance_store = instance;
06904                 }
06905             }
06906         }
06907         /* end exception */
06908 
06909         if (py_class_instance == NULL)
06910             py_srna = pyrna_struct_CreatePyObject(ptr);
06911 
06912         if (py_class_instance) {
06913             /* special case, instance is cached */
06914         }
06915         else if (py_srna == NULL) {
06916             py_class_instance = NULL;
06917         }
06918         else if (py_srna == Py_None) { /* probably wont ever happen but possible */
06919             Py_DECREF(py_srna);
06920             py_class_instance = NULL;
06921         }
06922         else {
06923 #if 1
06924             /* Skip the code below and call init directly on the allocated 'py_srna'
06925              * otherwise __init__() always needs to take a second self argument, see pyrna_struct_new().
06926              * Although this is annoying to have to implement a part of pythons typeobject.c:type_call().
06927              */
06928             if (py_class->tp_init) {
06929 #ifdef USE_PEDANTIC_WRITE
06930                 const int prev_write = rna_disallow_writes;
06931                 rna_disallow_writes = is_operator ? FALSE : TRUE; /* only operators can write on __init__ */
06932 #endif
06933 
06934                 /* true in most cases even when the class its self doesn't define an __init__ function. */
06935                 args = PyTuple_New(0);
06936                 if (py_class->tp_init(py_srna, args, NULL) < 0) {
06937                     Py_DECREF(py_srna);
06938                     py_srna = NULL;
06939                     /* err set below */
06940                 }
06941                 Py_DECREF(args);
06942 #ifdef USE_PEDANTIC_WRITE
06943                 rna_disallow_writes = prev_write;
06944 #endif
06945             }
06946             py_class_instance = py_srna;
06947 
06948 #else
06949             const int prev_write = rna_disallow_writes;
06950             rna_disallow_writes = TRUE;
06951 
06952             /* 'almost' all the time calling the class isn't needed.
06953              * We could just do... */
06954 #if 0
06955             py_class_instance = py_srna;
06956             Py_INCREF(py_class_instance);
06957 #endif
06958             /*
06959              * This would work fine but means __init__ functions wouldnt run.
06960              * none of blenders default scripts use __init__ but its nice to call it
06961              * for general correctness. just to note why this is here when it could be safely removed.
06962              */
06963             args = PyTuple_New(1);
06964             PyTuple_SET_ITEM(args, 0, py_srna);
06965             py_class_instance = PyObject_Call(py_class, args, NULL);
06966             Py_DECREF(args);
06967 
06968             rna_disallow_writes = prev_write;
06969 
06970 #endif
06971 
06972             if (py_class_instance == NULL) {
06973                 err = -1; /* so the error is not overridden below */
06974             }
06975             else if (py_class_instance_store) {
06976                 *py_class_instance_store = py_class_instance;
06977                 Py_INCREF(py_class_instance);
06978             }
06979         }
06980     }
06981 
06982     if (err != -1 && (is_static || py_class_instance)) { /* Initializing the class worked, now run its invoke function */
06983         PyObject *item = PyObject_GetAttrString((PyObject *)py_class, RNA_function_identifier(func));
06984 //      flag = RNA_function_flag(func);
06985 
06986         if (item) {
06987             RNA_pointer_create(NULL, &RNA_Function, func, &funcptr);
06988 
06989             args = PyTuple_New(rna_function_arg_count(func)); /* first arg is included in 'item' */
06990 
06991             if (is_static) {
06992                 i = 0;
06993             }
06994             else {
06995                 PyTuple_SET_ITEM(args, 0, py_class_instance);
06996                 i = 1;
06997             }
06998 
06999             RNA_parameter_list_begin(parms, &iter);
07000 
07001             /* parse function parameters */
07002             for (; iter.valid; RNA_parameter_list_next(&iter)) {
07003                 parm = iter.parm;
07004                 flag = RNA_property_flag(parm);
07005 
07006                 /* only useful for single argument returns, we'll need another list loop for multiple */
07007                 if (flag & PROP_OUTPUT) {
07008                     ret_len++;
07009                     if (pret_single == NULL) {
07010                         pret_single = parm;
07011                         retdata_single = iter.data;
07012                     }
07013 
07014                     continue;
07015                 }
07016 
07017                 parmitem = pyrna_param_to_py(&funcptr, parm, iter.data);
07018                 PyTuple_SET_ITEM(args, i, parmitem);
07019                 i++;
07020             }
07021 
07022 #ifdef USE_PEDANTIC_WRITE
07023             rna_disallow_writes = is_readonly ? TRUE : FALSE;
07024 #endif
07025             /* *** Main Caller *** */
07026 
07027             ret = PyObject_Call(item, args, NULL);
07028 
07029             /* *** Done Calling *** */
07030 
07031 #ifdef USE_PEDANTIC_WRITE
07032             rna_disallow_writes = FALSE;
07033 #endif
07034 
07035             RNA_parameter_list_end(&iter);
07036             Py_DECREF(item);
07037             Py_DECREF(args);
07038         }
07039         else {
07040             PyErr_Print();
07041             PyErr_Clear();
07042             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
07043                          "could not find function %.200s in %.200s to execute callback",
07044                          RNA_function_identifier(func), RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type));
07045             err = -1;
07046         }
07047     }
07048     else {
07049         /* the error may be already set if the class instance couldn't be created */
07050         if (err != -1) {
07051             PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
07052                          "could not create instance of %.200s to call callback function %.200s",
07053                          RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type), RNA_function_identifier(func));
07054             err = -1;
07055         }
07056     }
07057 
07058     if (ret == NULL) { /* covers py_class_instance failing too */
07059         err = -1;
07060     }
07061     else {
07062         if (ret_len == 0 && ret != Py_None) {
07063             PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
07064                          "expected class %.200s, function %.200s to return None, not %.200s",
07065                          RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type), RNA_function_identifier(func),
07066                          Py_TYPE(ret)->tp_name);
07067             err = -1;
07068         }
07069         else if (ret_len == 1) {
07070             err = pyrna_py_to_prop(&funcptr, pret_single, retdata_single, ret, "");
07071 
07072             /* when calling operator funcs only gives Function.result with
07073              * no line number since the func has finished calling on error,
07074              * re-raise the exception with more info since it would be slow to
07075              * create prefix on every call (when there are no errors) */
07076             if (err == -1) {
07077                 PyC_Err_Format_Prefix(PyExc_RuntimeError,
07078                                       "class %.200s, function %.200s: incompatible return value ",
07079                                       RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type), RNA_function_identifier(func));
07080             }
07081         }
07082         else if (ret_len > 1) {
07083 
07084             if (PyTuple_Check(ret) == 0) {
07085                 PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
07086                              "expected class %.200s, function %.200s to return a tuple of size %d, not %.200s",
07087                              RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type), RNA_function_identifier(func),
07088                              ret_len, Py_TYPE(ret)->tp_name);
07089                 err = -1;
07090             }
07091             else if (PyTuple_GET_SIZE(ret) != ret_len) {
07092                 PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
07093                              "class %.200s, function %.200s to returned %d items, expected %d",
07094                              RNA_struct_identifier(ptr->type), RNA_function_identifier(func),
07095                              PyTuple_GET_SIZE(ret), ret_len);
07096                 err = -1;
07097             }
07098             else {
07099 
07100                 RNA_parameter_list_begin(parms, &iter);
07101 
07102                 /* parse function parameters */
07103                 for (i = 0; iter.valid; RNA_parameter_list_next(&iter)) {
07104                     parm = iter.parm;
07105                     flag = RNA_property_flag(parm);
07106 
07107                     /* only useful for single argument returns, we'll need another list loop for multiple */
07108                     if (flag & PROP_OUTPUT) {
07109                         err = pyrna_py_to_prop(&funcptr, parm, iter.data,
07110                                                PyTuple_GET_ITEM(ret, i++),
07111                                                "calling class function:");
07112                         if (err) {
07113                             break;
07114                         }
07115                     }
07116                 }
07117 
07118                 RNA_parameter_list_end(&iter);
07119             }
07120         }
07121         Py_DECREF(ret);
07122     }
07123 
07124     if (err != 0) {
07125         ReportList *reports;
07126         /* alert the user, else they wont know unless they see the console. */
07127         if ((!is_static) &&
07128             (ptr->data) &&
07129             (RNA_struct_is_a(ptr->type, &RNA_Operator)) &&
07130             (is_valid_wm == (CTX_wm_manager(C) != NULL)))
07131         {
07132             wmOperator *op = ptr->data;
07133             reports = op->reports;
07134         }
07135         else {
07136             /* wont alert users but they can view in 'info' space */
07137             reports = CTX_wm_reports(C);
07138         }
07139 
07140         BPy_errors_to_report(reports);
